studentEssay: Recently, the number of people travelling abroad have increased. It is because there was the advance of transportation and economy. Many people want to go abroad for their own reasons. This is not except for students. I already saw some of my friend who study abroad. Why do they prefer abroad studying? I think there are 4 major reasons about it. First, we can get higher quality of education. Generally, there are more helpful programs for us in there. We can take an advantage through these programs. Second, It is good for learning language. By communicating with natives, we can improve our language skills very fast. Third, living in foreign country provide new experiences. During abroad studying, we can make our own unique experiences. Finally, we can overcome a lot of difficulties. There are maybe many difficulties because of new environment. We can be an adult while overcoming these difficulties. Then, should we study abroad for our future? I say, "No.". Even though there are many advantages of abroad studying, the choice must be determined carefully depending on your circumstance. So, you don't have to study abroad if it is not necessary for you. The most important thing is not abroad studying but yourself studying hard.

How do you think about this topic, "visual media influence people`s behavior positively or negatively?" I think "posively".
First, certain TV program or visual media teach audiences certain knowledge which normal people cannot know well. For example, we can learn about laws about car accident from TV program which uses blackbox real video and appears real lawyer. And also we can learn child mind form a program which doctor and medical professor, mind counsilors are charactors.
Second, I experienced many various feelings. When I watch the movie or drama, I can be a pilot, rich person, chinese or man. Then I can feel special feeling which I cannot feel or do in real life. Many people including me feel various feeling(angry, happy, sad or confused) and grow more mutually. And watchers can go back to 2002 then they all experience Olimpic Soccer. We can experience not only present but also past and future.
Lastly, we can know recent trend  about politics, clothing and economy. I often watch TV advertisements and I refer them when I go to shopping. And in News program, they tell about today`s global festival or political issue from very various country.
I think visual media influence people`s behavior positively. Visual media can give us certain professonal knowledge and various special feelings experience. And visual media influence many people about global fashion or political trend. In these reason, I suggest vidual media influence very positively.

studentEssay: In these days, some people say there should be a 4-day work week. And new Kodea president also does similar project, 4.5-day work week. But, does it really efficient for our society? I think there should be many things to be considered. First, isn't there loss to company? In country, there are a lot of companies, and there are also a lot of people who work in companies more than companies exist. People who say there should be a 4-day work week mainly say there will not be loss to companies because people with 4-day work week will work harder than 5-day work week. But 24-hour is not small time. Companies fight with another companies, and country's main industry fights with other country's companies. If we do 4-day work week project while other countries still do 5-day work week, we could lose our competitiveness. Second, if there be loss in companies, country which makes money by tax also takes a hit. In conclusion, we should consider many pros and cons to make our society better.

studentEssay:
The reading presents three possible solutions to save the Torreya tree from extinction. However, in the lecture, the professor disagrees with all of them and explains why they are unlikely to work. First, the reading suggests replanting the Torreya tree in its original habitat in Florida, where it used to grow well because of a special microclimate. But the professor says that climate change has changed the region, and the microclimate no longer exists. So, putting the tree back in that area will not help. 
Second, the reading proposes moving Torreya to a new, colder region in the north. The idea is that Torreya might grow better in that kind of climate. The professor disagrees and gives an example of the black locust tree. It was moved to a new area and grew too fast, causing damage to the local ecosystem. 
Finally, the reading recommends growing Torreya in research centers. This way, scientists can protect and study the tree. However, the professor argues that trees kept in such places lose their natural resistance to diseases. Also, it's difficult to recreate the large and diverse environment that the tree needs to survive in the wild.

revised_essay:
The reading passage presents three potential solutions to prevent the extinction of the Torreya tree. However, the professor in the lecture disagrees with all of them and provides reasons why they are unlikely to be effective.
First, the reading suggests replanting the Torreya tree in its original habitat in Florida, where a unique microclimate once supported its growth. The professor, however, points out that due to climate change, this microclimate no longer exists, making the reintroduction of the tree to this area ineffective.
Second, the reading proposes relocating the Torreya tree to a colder region in the north, assuming that it may thrive in such a climate. The professor counters this by citing the example of the black locust tree, which, after being moved to a new area, grew excessively and caused damage to the local ecosystem.
Finally, the reading recommends cultivating the Torreya tree in research centers, enabling scientists to protect and study it. Nevertheless, the professor argues that trees grown in controlled environments tend to lose their natural resistance to diseases. Furthermore, replicating the extensive and diverse conditions required for the tree’s survival in the wild is highly challenging.

studentEssay:
TITLE: There should be a 4-day work week.

Many foreign workers in Korea have a difficulty in something. Can you guess what it is? It’s working hour (time). They usually have had hard time to adopt Korea working system. Korea works too much. Even though it decreased than before, the A of Korean work up to 55 hours per week. So, today, I’ll discuss why There should be a 4-day work week. Now, I’ll give you more details.

To begin with, we can do more in work if we get relax more. Think about When you take over the night studying. Was the efficiency good? Maybe not. It’s same as workers. They should get relax more, take a sleep and then come to work place with high quality of energy and condition.

Secondly, if there is a 4-day work week, the increasing of spending would be expected. Spending could be a good for economics. Many can cycle and small marketers can sell more things. For example, Past in Korea, when it changed to 5-day work week from 6-day work week, Many people worried that workers efficiency will get down. However, people spend a lot of time and Money so the economics could be circulated.

Lastly, it can be welfare to workers time take off one day. They do not need to use their personal holiday to their work place. Everybody get a break. So, people can live more happily.

Then, how to make it for real? I’ll suggest some ways to bring it.
First way: work free on wednesday. If we take a break on wednesday, we only work two days directly. Wednesday is profit for holiday because it located middle of weeks days.
Second way: replace work free days zig-zag. For example, people whose birth-year ends with 0,5 → Mon, 1,6 → Tue, 2,7 → Wednesday, 3,8 → Thur, 4,9 → Fri work free.

Secondly, if we read various books, the increasing of knowledge can be expected. More knowledge could be advantage for job. Many can understand new concepts and small discussions become easier. Past in history, when new kinds of literature appeared, many thought it’s not efficient. But, people gain insight so knowledge expand widely.

Lastly, books are important for every age in life. No one need to have special book or special shelf. Everybody find a story they like. So, people can have more joy.

So, how to make reading a more popular habit? I’ll offer some ideas.

First idea: read as group on weekend. If we read together on saturday, it make the activity social. 
Second idea: read based by year of experience. For example, people with 5 year of reading experience: classic, 2 year: fiction, and new readers: start with short stories.

Nowadays, there are the discussions about the 4-day work week. Some people say 4-day work week improves the efficiency of the work, but the other say it won't work because of several reasons. In my opinion, there shouldn't be a 4-day work week. Let's talk about some reasons on my opinion.
 First, the total amount of work may decrease if 4-day work week is conducted. This causes decrease of domestic production and national competiveness.
 Second, people try to rest somehow. The word 'work-life balance' appear recently. It means that people need to balance between work and life. In other words, people already know how to rest while they work.
 Third, there is no evidence that 4-day work week improves the efficiency of the work. To rest is very important, but many restness make people lazy. So, there is no correlation between 4-day work week and improvement of the work performance. 
 There are several reasons why there shouldn't be a 4-day work week. The total work amount decreases, people already try to rest, there is no evidence about the improvement of the work performance, etc. So, there shouldn't be a 4-day work week.

I believe that automobiles have largely benefit peoples in todays world. 
One advantage that automobiles bring is that it saves time. Cars, bus ,even airplanes and helocopters can be used to travel way faster than previously used ways such by horse or by foot.
However some may argue that these industrial machines pollute the nature, which is true but with enviromental engineers and other specialist working to reduce it and with the incoming of electric vehicles i believe it will decrease.
Another pros of automobiles is it fits the modern life or it will be difficult imagine the paved roads and skyscappers without it as these vehicle birth basically resulted them.
So, due to time saving factor and further improving vehicle, well fit design and role in modern life i believe automobiles improved modern life.

studentEssay:
Can't we just work 4days per week?
Yes we can't. I firmly believe that we have to work 5 days per week. There are two main reasons about it : Economic depression and society problems. Let's go deeply about these. 
The first main reason is Economic depression. Economic system will be damaged in many ways if we change into 4-day work. For example, companies will lose their efficiency of producing, and many people will lose their job. And it will leaded to economic depression.
The second main reason is about laws and society problems. Since many laws are fitted to 5-day working, the change must involve a change of laws too. During the law-changing days, people may feel confused. And it can be leaded to some society problems such as sabotage.
For these reasons, we can't work only 4 days per week. Maybe 4-day working is great, but our society is not ready to accept such a big change. 
Thank you for reading.

studentEssay:
In many countries, labors, workers and many people who literally "works" are expecting two days every week, which is Saturday and Sunday. The reason is simple. As everyone knows those who days are the only days on week to be free from work and rest and chill. But some of the people think that two days for rest isn't enough. Some of them argue we should suppose to have 4-day work week, not 5-day work week as usual. This sounds cool to many workers, so for the happiness of many people this argument looks persuasive and positive. But however, changing the policy dramatically "for" the people convey side effects in high possibility. What kinds of side effects will this argument have?
To say extremely economy system could collapse. The world is based on 5-day work week now. Through many researchers and histories people believed 2 free work days are enough and the countries selected that policy. However let's suppose that one country change it to 4-day work week, so every companies should give workers 3 free days. First thing that will happen is that the GDP of the country will decrease. This will happen naturally because the time for working has been decreased. Then how about the boss make workers harder to prohibit this situation? Well, I believe this could be more stressful for workers than 5-day work week.

Music is an integral part of our daily lives in globalisation, serves for entertainment, emotional relief, therapy, and more. It accessibly enters our space through platforms like Spotify, radio, YouTube, and music apps. However, not everyone parses this art form thoroughly to understand its depth, message, or cultural implications, which can be especially risky without critical listening. Thus, I argue that music significantly influences people's emotions and perspectives, which is suggested in the subsequent text.

To commence with, people should develop a nuanced appreciation for music's cultural significance and message. Various songs depict themes such as love, violence, and social topics, often clashing with one's personal beliefs. Take for example, rap music—a genre that openly discusses societal issues such as racial disparity and economic struggles. Some listeners might interpret these issues superficially, thinking, "This is the lifestyle to aspire to!" which might distort their perception, not to be banned but needs mature understanding.

Moreover, critically interpreting music's lyrics requires astute thinking, such as identifying the authenticity of an artist's message or intentions. Notably, social media platforms where artists share their songs without filters can cause widespread beliefs based on unstated ideas, leading to unfounded opinions.

Furthermore, the ease of music streaming enables individuals to indulge habitually, overconsuming media to the extent that they neglect important responsibilities. This overindulgence can often interfere with one's productivity and prioritisation of tasks, reducing overall effectiveness in managing their routines.

Altogether, there are several potential benefits and detriments to absorbing music's power without analysis, although maturity can develop towards balanced consumption.

The "Chusuck" holiday is just a month left. Like me, everyone is starting to prepare for a long journey to their hometown: Searching for any rest train or bus seats, get enough oils for their cars, or maybe reserving an airplane ticket. Now let's think about how would us make the long marathon to our hometown if we didn't have all these automobiles. We might have to walk all the way down, which would take more than a week, for sure. As you can see, the automobile has improved our life a lot, and I will show you some more examples throughout this passage. 

 Back in the days, when there was some important news in the country, it tooke a lot of times to get people know it since the country is too big to move around just with a horse or something. After the automobile came out, it became much easier to send recent news across the country. The best improvement that the automobile made is that we could save a lot of times - not just for people, but also for letters, foods, products, etc. 

 The automobile made our society way better, too. The shorter time taken to move means more chances to meet friends who lives in the opposite side of the country and more time for work or entertainment. This improved the social activity in human society and also the quality of human's life.

 Didn't had enough time for the conclusion, sadly, so I would write some short one: automobile surely improved our modern life, and the human society.

With the popularity of technology, computer has changed our life. Today, nearly everybody use computer for work, study, or entertainment. Even though there are some issues concerns computers, it isn't mean computers should be avoided. Computers strongly affect our daily life on good side. There is three reasons why I say this.

First, computer allows people to access information from all around the world. It enables them to learn about topics that are significant for them. And it even make connections between people stronger by using online platforms. That is, computer give us positive outcomes by letting access to informations that are far from us.

Second, computer is deeply related with communication. Communication is vital for develop societies. It helps countries be able to exchange ideas and culture with others. And it also assist people's daily life to be easier. Then, computer gives opportunity to communicate to different societies.

Lastly, computer improves the ways people view the world. Through computers, people can interact with experts worldwide. During this process, people share opinions with others who live in different culture than us. And it grants us a worldwide view.

In conclusion, there are numerous benefits about computers like broadening knowledge, facilitating communication, and a global perspective. Even though there are some negative points about computers, these positive contributions cannot be dismissed. Therefore, computer is an essential component to advance the contemporary life.

We can experience not only present but also past and future.
Lastly, we can know recent trend  about politics, clothing and economy. I often watch TV advertisements and I refer them when I go to shopping. And in News program, they tell about today`s global festival or political issue from very various country.
I think visual media influence people`s behavior positively. Visual media can give us certain professonal knowledge and various special feelings experience. And visual media influence many people about global fashion or political trend. In these reason, I suggest vidual media influence very positively.

I don't think 4-day work week is neceserry. It can be choosed in some companies if they need, but it should not be restricted in law. There are two reasons, First, 4-day work week is only for the empoloyees. Maybe there is a buesiness that need people 5 or more day a weel. Susch companies will be highly harmed if people only work 4 day a week.
Second, some workers would not like this policy to worker's labor are depend on how much time day work. And work less day means less working time and also less money. So wokers that value money than rest would not like those policy. I think it would be good if some copanies that don't need people 5-days a week decide to there empoloyees to work only 4 or 3 days a week. then empoloyees who want to work less would go to those companies. And empoloyees who wants to work more and get money will go to other companies. And company is also happy because they would give less money to there empoloyees. Because of the reasons above, I don't think 4 day work week should be forced

Title: We can't live without communication devices.

There is a lot of issue created by smartphones. About 5 years ago, there was a major internet blackout in South Korea. Society was disrupted and numerous businesses were affected. Many people remember it for about 5 years. Last month, there was a massive data breach and many people's privacy was compromised. Like these examples, communication devices can cause serious problems. However I believe they are crucial to our life.

First, we can connect with others easily with mobile phones. Everyday I use smartphone to contact my family and friends. Without mobile phones, I would have to send letters and wait days for a response. With communication devices, we can connect with people worldwide effortlessly.

Second, communication devices can assist in emergencies. If there's medical emergency, you can call for help immediately. If someone is stranded in remote area, a phone can alert rescue teams to locate them. We can contact specialist doctor for advice if needed. We can share information instantly. All these are possible because of communication devices.

Finally, issue started by phones isn't their fault. We aware of electricity. However no one think electricity is the one to be exitted from our life. Communication devices is similar to electricity. It is risky but it is essential. Issue arise due to not device but user.

Therefore, communication devices enable us to connect easily, provide assistance in emergencies, and issues aren’t caused by devices themselves. For these reasons, communication devices have enhanced our lifestyle. If we utilize wisely, we can minimize serious issue. We can't live without communication devices.

studentEssay:
Do you know why the week take 7 days? For a long time ago our acients believe that "7" is the perfect number of harmony. So they choose 7 days for one week. This is why we work 5 days a week rest for 2 days. However, as time passes and people care about the effiency and work - life balance,some people suggest a 4-day work week which make one week into 6 days. For this state, I disagree with this state for 3 reasons.
First of all, "Monday illness" will be worse. In Korea, every students and workers have "Monday illness" which is they feel tired on Monsday after they rest for Saturday and Sunday. If there's a 4-day work week, we will rest more than a 5-day work week. Then, our tiredness and bothering will be worse.
Second, originally we spend 5 days for work in 7days. It means we work 5/7. If there was 4-day work week, then we work only 2/3. As we work less, the company will make a profit less. Rhen, we might work on Saturday or Sunday, too. Working on weekend maek people feel much worse, so I disagree with 4-day work week.
In conclusion, I disagree with 4-day work week for worse of "Monday illness" and working weekend.If we try to change original system, we have to think deeply what this will cause.

studentEssay: In my opinion, 4-day work week is not good for us. There are three reasons. First, if we take a rest three days a week, it is difficult to focus on working again. Anyone can think deep break time makes high work efficiency. However, I think two days are regular break time for coming back to working completely. Second, it can cause economic problems. Economies of country is moved by many companies. If we work only 4 days a week, regardless for working efficiency, income of company will decline exactly. Because 5 days that we can work for reduce to 4 days. Then, naturally income of country will reduce, and economy will be bad. It is a important problem to think about before talking about working efficiency. Finally, sleeping patterns of employees can cause several problems. Original way that taking a rest for two days is so short that can't change sleeping patterns of employees. In weekend, we often watch TV late or drink late, then pattern breaks. In contrast, three days are enough to change sleeping pattern. So it can affect to working like take a nap while working. Based on these three reasons. I think 4-day work week is not good.

revised_essay:
TITLE: Don't need a A day wont week
I think a four-day work week is not needed. Firstly, it will not only be unhelpful but also make the situation worse. With a longer weekend, the free time will increase, but the amount of work that a company should complete in a month does not change. Therefore, we must complete the same amount of work in a shorter period. It causes many health problems, border working life, and a lot of working at night. Eventually, a four-day work week cannot achieve its goal of making life better by providing a longer weekend.

Second, there can be many opinions that support a five-day work and two-day weekend system. It has already become a social standard. Every school and college follows that rule. But if students go to school only four days a week, it will reduce learning and cause the loss of many genius students who could lead a country.

Third, harder work brings many health problems. I wrote a short essay, but it is a very important problem. The worst problem is a lack of sleep. Experts suggest people sleep 8 hours a day, but we already cannot follow that. It may hurt more than before, and many will sleep under 5 hours in a day. A lack of sleep destroys our immune system and leads to a higher chance of many diseases, including cancer. Some may say that we can sleep more in the 3-day rest, but it will make the situation worse. We should sleep in balance.

Music has been an important part in our life for a very long time. There are variety of musics in the world today, offering us both entertainment and reflection. But, I think music often affect people emotions in different ways.
 First, fast and loud music can cause people to become anxious. When people listen to music with fast beat and loud volume, it can increase their heart rates and make them feel stress. These kinds of feelings lead particular young adults to experience nervous situations.
 Second, repetitive music, such as pop songs, can make the focus of people low. People can constantly listen to the same repetitive sounds and may find it hard to pay attention to other tasks. Then, this behavior can stop the brain from concentrating on important matters.
 Lasts, music lyrics can give people incorrect informations. With the growth of lyric platforms, obtaining the words of a song become easily. However, not all song lyrics provide accurate ideas, so it can lead people to misunderstand reality.
 For such reasons, music may have unrestricted impact on our emotions, I hope music will contribute positive values to the society.

studentEssay:
In many countries, laborers, workers, and many people who literally "work" are expecting two days every week, which are Saturday and Sunday. The reason is simple. As everyone knows, those days are the only days in the week to be free from work and rest and chill. But some of the people think that two days for rest isn't enough. Some of them argue we should have a 4-day work week, not a 5-day work week as usual. This sounds cool to many workers, so for the happiness of many people, this argument looks persuasive and positive. However, changing the policy dramatically "for" the people conveys side effects with a high possibility. What kinds of side effects will this argument have?
To say an extremely economic system could collapse. The world is based on a 5-day work week now. Through many researchers and historians, people believed 2 free work days are enough, and the countries selected that policy. However, let's suppose that one country changes it to a 4-day work week, so every company should give workers 3 free days. The first thing that will happen is that the GDP of the country will decrease. This will happen naturally because the time for working has been decreased. Then, how about the boss make workers harder to prevent this situation? Well, I believe this could be more stressful for workers than a 5-day work week.

In nowadays, there are a lot of automobiles, such as cars, trains, or airplane. For now, so many people have their own cars, and travel to other country by airplane or train. Some people think the automobile has caused problems, such as accidents, or enviorment pollusion. However, I think automobile is the main factor of modern life, so it is essential for our life. First of all, we can move so fast by automobile. it is not just for people. What we eat and use can be also delivered. So we can eat fruits or other food from other country, which people couldn't eat before. And we can trade so many countries and get various things that we can't get in our countries. Second reason is the economic effect. For example, car industry make a lot of jobs. Car manufactoring industry needs so many people to work, so many people get job in this industry. And thanks to automobile, we can go abroad easily. so trip industry has improved, and it aslo has made huge economic effects. if countries have good factor that can attract travlers, they can earn a lot of money. These all thing can be done due to automobile. Lastly, it made moving more comfortable, so not only normal people, but also disabled people that hard to move for their own can move comfortably. Although people can't move, now they can move anywhere by automobile.
In conclusion, even though automobile cause some problems, its value is much more important, and it is essential for our life.

studentEssay:
Many people who incloud my parent, friends want to do 4-day work week and get 3-day weekend. Sometime I want that, too when I feel tired because of busy weekday. However, I don't agrre that we have to get 4 day work week. There are two reasons why I don't agree that.

First reason is that we are more busy and tired in weekday if we do 4-day work. Many people who want it think that if 4-day work is accepted, our work time is reduced, so it is more free than before. But, in fact, the amount of work in a week is similar with before. It makes to increase the density of weekday and us feel tired and busy. In my case, I felt more busy and difficult when I tried to finish my homework for getting more free time.
Finally, I think that we will feel hard to return weekday if a length of weekend is increse. I have seen that almost people felt more hard when they got much holiday than weekend. In my case, The size of my mind which I don’t want to return classes is bigger weekend than vacation.
A 4-day work week is looked like reducing our work and giving us relax, but it give us increasing density of work time and more tired. So, I think we have to do 5-day work week.

Shopping online are very popular now. Many people enjoy to buy things on the internet because it's easy and convenient. But, I not agree that online shopping is the best way. There two reasons for it.

First, sometimes you receive the wrong item or it not like the picture showed online. Many friends of mine have bad experience with this. In fact, when you go to store, you can see and touch what you buy. It make you sure about what you getting.

Second reason, online shopping can make people lazy and not active. I heard that people who buy only online just stay at home and they don't go out often. This habit is not good for health. If people go to stores, they have to walk and maybe they exercise more.

To sum up, shopping online seem easy but it have problems too. People should think about good and bad sides before choose how they like to shop.

studentEssay:
Some people say that "5-day work week is too ling and 2-day weekend is too short". So, they argue that we need to change 5-day work week to 4-dsy work week. This opinion has lots of adventage and most people also want 4-day work week. But, I think this opinion has more disadvantage. So I disagree there should be 4-day work week.

First reason that I disagree is if there is 4-day work week, we need more work on week. When 5-day work week change 4-day work week, if we work same amount, result amount will decrease. So, we work more harder to fill decreased amount and this will lead to harder work in work week.

Second reason is we already have much time to spend our hobby time. Some people who agree 4-day work week argue that if we change work week, we spend enough time to enjoy hobby. But I think we already have enough time to spend our hobby time. Because when we rest on weekend, we consume enough time to exercise, watch movie, and so on. Moreover, we also have free time on work week when we finish the work.

For this reason, I think that we don’t have to change 5-day work week to 4-day work week. 5-day work week also has many free time and didn’t need harder work.

peerEssay:
In today's world, health is very important, but many people ignore it. They eat unhealthy foods and don’t exercise enough which can be problem. But, there are many people who wants to be healthy, and they try very hard to exercise and eat well. However, I think this is not enough because they didn’t have all information they need.

One main reason why people are not healthy is because they don’t have information about nutrition. When people eat, they only think about taste. If they don’t learn about nutrition, they still the same problem even if they exercise. So, they need specific details about foods they eat, to understand what is good for them and what is not.

Another reason is exercise routines are often not effective. People try their best to follow routines, but without correct guidance, they didn’t know if they improve or not. This can make them work more harder without result. If they have proper advice, they can improve health balance between their work and personal life.

In conclusion, I think health important but not easy. People must learn the true information about food and exercise properly. To have good health, they need to balance the both.

studentEssay:
Many people who incloud my parent, and friends want to do 4-day work week and get 3-day weekend. Sometime I would want that, too when I felt tired because of busy weekday. However, I don't agree that we have to get 4 day work week. There are two reasons why I don't agree that.

First reason is that we are more busy and tired in weekday if we do 4-day work. Many people who want it think that if 4-day work is accepted, their work time is reduced, so it is more free than before. But, in fact, the amount of work in a week is similar with before. It makes to increase the density of weekday and us feel tired and busy. In my case, I felt more busy and difficult when I tried to finish my homework for getting more free time.
Finally, I think that we will feel hard to return weekday if a length of weekend is incresed. I have seen that almost people felt more hard when they got much holiday than weekend. In my case, The size of my mind which I don’t want to return classes is bigger weekend than vacation.
A 4-day work week is looked like reducing our work and giving us relax, but it gives us increasing density of work time and more tired. So, I think we have to do 5-day work week.

Has automobiles improved modern life quality?
I believe that automobiles have largely benefit peoples in todays world. 
One advantage that automobiles bring is that it saves time. Cars, bus ,even airplanes and helocopters can be used to travel way faster than previously used ways such by horse or by foot.
However some may argue that these industrial machines pollute the nature, which is true but with enviromental engineers and other specialist working to reduce it and with the incoming of electric vehicles i believe it will decrease.
Another pros of automobiles is it fits the modern life or it will be difficult imagine the paved roads and skyscappers without it as these vehicle birth basically resulted them.
So, due to time saving factor and further improving vehicle, well fit design and role in modern life i believe automobiles improved modern life.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The way to make your life abundant, Studying abroad!

Today, I’m going to talk about studying abroad. Is studying abroad necessary for students? In my case, I think studying abroad makes our life better. This is a reason why I want to study abroad after graduation of college. These are some reasons which support my opinion.

First, studying abroad leads to new experience which your life abundant. If you go to other country, there are lots of things (including buildings, culture) not familiar with you. These may help you to get a new idea. Furthermore, not be limited in your hometown can make you get new eyesight. For example, in my case, I traveled to New York City, one of the biggest cities in the world, when I was in high school. To compare the difference between Seoul and New York City actually Seoul have developed too fast which makes the distribution of buildings a little complicated. In contrast, New York city have developed gradually which makes city organized. I also experience tip culture and at Smithsonian museum, I watched many sculpture of organisms that I had learned about during evolution and taxonomy class. So studying abroad help you to get a new experience.

Second, you can have a relationship with new people. Relationship is important because when you get in trouble, you can receive a support and encouragement from your people. For instance, when you do a business, a relationship with employers, other companies is essential to keep your business stable. So more various people you meet, more abundant your life.

To summarize, there are two benefits, new experience and relationship, of studying abroad. There should be a correlation between studying abroad and life quality, why don’t you go to abroad to get new friends and experience.

ESSAY TITLE: How to make your leisure time enjoyable, Exploring hobbies!

Today, I’m going to talk about exploring new hobbies. Is it necessary for everyone to have hobbies? In my case, I think exploring hobbies makes our life fun. This is a reason why I take up new hobbies during weekends. These are some reasons which support my opinion.

First, exploring hobbies leads to new joy which your leisure enriching. If you engage in different activities, there are lots of new skills (such as painting, cooking) not common for you. These may help you to get a new passion. Furthermore, not be confined to usual routine can make you get new happiness. For example, in my case, I started hiking in mountains, one of the most enjoyable activities in the world, when I was in college. To feel the difference between indoor and outdoor activities actually indoor activities become monotonous fastly which makes life a little boring. In contrast, outdoor activities change seasonally which makes them diverse. I also tried birdwatching and at local park, I saw many birds that I had learned about during biology class. So exploring hobbies help you to get a new joy.

Second, you can have a bond with new friends. Bonding is important because when you feeling lonely, you can receive a motivation and comfort from your friends. For example, when you join a club, a bond with members, other groups is essential to keep your interest active. So more various friends you meet, more joyful your leisure.

To summarize, there are two benefits, new joy and bond, of exploring hobbies. There should be a connection between hobbies and leisure quality, why don’t you explore new hobbies to get new friends and joy.

At nowdays, many people uses smartphones to communicate. For my point of view, these devices is not completely useful for us. Even if they help us connect and it's very convenient, it cause some issues.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The way to make your life abundant, Studying abroad!

Today, I’m going to talk about studying abroad. Is studying abroad necessary for students? In my case, I think studying abroad makes our life better. So I want to study abroad after graduation of college. These are some reasons which support my opinion.

First, studying abroad leads to new experience which makes your life abundant. If you go to other country, there are lots of things (including buildings, culture) not familiar with you. These may help you to get a new idea. Furthermore, not be limited in your hometown can make you get new eyesight. For example, in my case, I traveled to New York City, one of the biggest cities in the world, when I was in high school. To compare the difference between Seoul and New York City, actually Seoul have developed too fast which makes the distribution of buildings a little complicated. In contrast, New York city have developed gradually which makes city organized. I also experience tip culture and at Smithsonian museum, I watched many sculpture of organisms that I had learned about during evolution and taxonomy class. So studying abroad help you to get a new experience.

Second, you can have a relationship with new people. Relationship is important because when you get in trouble, you can receive a support and encouragement from your people. For instance, when you do a business, a relationship with employers, other companies is essential to keep your business stable. So more various people you meet, more abundant your life.

To summarize, there are two benefits, new experience and relationship, of studying abroad. There should be a correlation between studying abroad and life quality, why don’t you go to abroad to get new friends and experience.

ESSAY TITLE: Why Walking is an Incredible Exercise

Today, let me explain the benefits of walking. How often do we consider walking as exercise? In my case, I believe walking makes life more active. So I prefer to walk instead of using vehicle whenever possible. Let me provide reasons that support my view.

First, walking provide a way to relax and think clearly. Walking to somewhere, you notice many things like tree, sky, and sounds of nature not obvious in cars. These can give you peace of mind. Moreover, walking regularly make you feel better mentally. For example, my own experience, I used to walk around my neighborhood park every morning. To compare the stress level before and after walking, actually my stress decrease and I felt happy. In contrast, sitting inside whole day increase stress levels. I also met a man with his dog in the park, and we discussed many topics. So walking helps to give peace and clarity.

Second, you stay fit and healthy by walking. Health is crucial because when illness strikes, support and encouragement might come from unexpected places. For instance, reducing weight or maintaining a healthy heart can be enhanced by walking. Hence, more frequent you walk, more benefits you gain.

Finally, to sum up, there are a few advantages, clarity and health, of choosing to walk. There should be no doubt about walking and its positive impacts, why don’t you add walking into your daily routine for benefit and pleasure.

studentEssay:
Have you ever lived in a dormitory? Many people at KAIST have experienced living in dormitory. Depending on roommate, our life can be comfortable or uncomfortable. Then, what do you think are the qualities of a good roommate.
 I think there are three qualities of good roommate. 
 First, not be noisy. Do you know about biological time? Bio time is pattern of when we sleep, eat. It is important to keep rhythm. According to research, if bio time is broken, expect life decreases. Therefore, we have to be respect bio time of our roommate. But each people have various bio time. When you talk with your friends, somebody is sleeping. So we should be quiet to be respect bio time of our roommate.
 Second, be clear. When I was 17, in high school, I have dirty roommate. He didn't take a shower, throw something which he had eaten. Our room is dirtier, and finally we don't have enough space to do something and smell like garbage can. This is the worst experience in my life. After this experience, I think cleanliness is very important. So I think when we live with somebody, we should be clear.
 Lastly, be respect privacy time. Even though we live with somebody, we want privacy time. If we can't be respect privacy time, we will be tired and maybe fight with roommate. Privacy time is one of the most important in life. It is can increase creativity, and be charge energy to work. So we should be respect privacy time.
 I think these three things are the most important qualities of roommate because these things are to be respect our roommate. If you are quiet, clear, and respect to privacy time, you will be good roommate.

studentEssay:
In nowadays, there are a lot of automobiles, such as cars, trains, or airplanes. For now, so many people have their own cars, and travel to other country by airplane or train. Some people think the automobile has caused problems, such as accidents, or environment pollution. However, I think automobile is the main factor of modern life, so it is essential for our life. First of all, we can move so fast by automobile. it is not just for people. What we eat and use can be also delivered. So we can eat fruits or other food from other country, which people couldn't eat before. And we can trade so many countries and get various things that we can't get in our countries. Second reason is the economic effect. For example, car industry make a lot of jobs. Car manufacturing industry needs so many people to work, so many people get job in this industry. And thanks to automobile, we can go abroad easily. so trip industry has improved, and it also has made huge economic effects. if countries have good factor that can attract travelers, they can earn a lot of money. These all thing can be done due to automobile. Lastly, it made moving more comfortable, so not only normal people, but also disabled people that hard to move for their own can move comfortably. Although people can't move, now they can move anywhere by automobile.
In conclusion, even though automobile cause some problems, its value is much more important, and it is essential for our life.

In recent days, technology change our life in many way. For now, people use phone to communication, watch video, and play game. Some people say technology cause problem, like addiction, and makes us lazy. But I believe technology improve our live overall, and is now a necessary part of it. Firstly, we can find information so fast with internet. it is not just for young generation. Old people can learn new things and stay connected with family far away. So, people become more knowledgeable and informed about world. Technology also made education is accessible to all, even in remote area. Second benefit is the connection it offers. For example, social media let us meet many people. This make it easy to stay in touch with friends or meet coworker for project. And with phone, we can have meeting or talk to client anywhere. Because of this, many businesses have grow and connect global markets. if a firm has good service or product, it can reach many customer's fast. Third, it help everyday task convenient, so not only young people, but also older people who find hard to shop can order things online. Even if they are home, now they can get anything delivered rapidly.
In conclusion, while technology bring some challenges, it has greater importance and crucial to our daily activities.

studentEssay:
Many university students consider whether they have to study abroad. Some students apply being an exchange student, other students study in only their contries. In my opinion, I think that students should study abroad. Let me explain three reasons.
 First of all, students can experience various views. For example, in France, mathematics is based on logic which France has only. Therefore, if students study in country which has it's own advantages in students' interested field, they can experience various views. 
 Second, students can learn from famous professor. For example, in other country, there are Dokinson, Karl Seigon, Michael Sandel, who are famous people in their fields. However, there are few chances to meet them in students' countries. Therefore, if students study in country which has famous professor, they can learn many things.
 Lastly, students can take part in a symposium of subject in which they are interested. There are many symposiums of various subjects in other countries. Students can share their paper, review other's paper, and communicate their opinion and feedback. So, if students take part in a symposium in other countries, they can improve their research skills.
 For these reasons, I think that students should study abroad. It will make students experience various views, learn from famous professor, take part in a symposium of subject in which they are interested.

studentEssay: I believe there should be a 4-day work week and a 3-day off week every week. There are several reasons for this. First, people can't work productively unless they relax enough. Only two days off is a very small range to take a good nap. Second, everyone works to live a happy life, but if you have only two days to spend with your family, in my opinion, it is not enough to bring happiness. Besides, Sunday can't be counted as a full holiday, because the reason for this is Monday, when everyone needs to go to work. So everyone tries to sleep early as as early as they can, which means Sunday is not a full holiday. Because of the above reasons, I think there should be 3 days off every week.

studentEssay:
In contemporary societies, we are exposed to many visual medias like movies, TV, netflix, and YouTube. Nowadays, most people can access to these visual medias easily, so they become part of our life. And they give some new information, dopamine by watching them. But is this really good for life?

Some dopamine may be needed for us, of course. But most visual medias give more dopamine then enough amount to us. Visual medias are very fateful interesting, so we chintly watch more and more. Imagine the situation that the person watching YouTube shorts and it’s time to sleep. This person may think “I will sleep after this video end”. But dopamine from video makes this person to see other video naturally. Although person turn off the phone, He(or she) think about Youtube video, so He(or she) cannot sleep early. Also too many dopamines decrease our concentration. When you study after watch the visual media, you may think about what you see, so you cannot focus on study only, this may reduce your work ability. Supporting this opinion, the person who stop watching viusal medias and cut all dopamine, much more fastly his work.

And getting information by visual media can be dangerous. Of course, there are many useful information in visual media. But you should remember there are many wrong information. Even, added movie animation, with wrong information, people are more easily belive that wrong information.

For this reason, we should reduce our time that watching visual medias and increase our life quality.

peerEssay:
In modern world, transportation is a important part of life. Cars, buses, trains, and airplanes are common transport methods we use every day. Nowadays, people can access to fast cars easily, so they become essential for our daily activities. And they provide ways to navigate city quickly. But is this reliance on cars good for environment?

Of course, transport are necessary for mobility. But most cars release more pollution then acceptable levels to atmosphere. Vehicles provide to us convenience, so we frequently use them more and more. Imagine a city where everyone driving cars, and it’s rush hour. Many person think “I’ll reach destination soon.” But traffic from too many vehicles causes to delays naturally. Although some people prefer public transport, he (or she) still stuck in traffic and cannot arrive on time.

Also, increased pollution affect our health. When you walk after breathe polluted air, you may feel tiredness, so you cannot exercise properly, reducing your fitness ability. Supporting this opinion, people who cycle instead of drive car improve health, more fastly they lose weight.

Moreover, road infrastructures can be dangerous too. Of course, there are many safe roads and bridges. But it should remember accidents happen because of bad maintenance. Even, constructed highways with poor planning lead to traffic congestions, and people are more easily become frustrated.

For this reason, we should reduce our car usage and expand public transport to improve quality of life.

In conclusion, 4-day work week can give people not only time to refresh but also effective working time. If there is 4-day work week, people feel cheerful and do their work well.

  First, 2 days to holiday are very short and unbalanced. We work 5 days and rest 2 days, than it can't give perfact rest for us. If we aren't take a rest efficient, we can't work efficiently, also. That is not good for all of us.
  Second, we need to time for self-training. We do not only work but also self-training. For example, we can spend time for learning about programming, singing or writing some books, etc. These times make your skills development and raise your work efficiency.
  Lastly, we don't need to work harder than before. AI can do many simple works faster than people. So, we don't need to work long time. We have to concentrate our own work and have to think what should we do and what AI can't do. We train our mind and have creativity more than before.
  In conclusion, for three reasons, I think that we need 4-day work week. Todays system is not efficient for work and we have to spend time for not only works also self-training. 4-day work gives times people to take some rest and develop some skills. I hope it will be changed to 4-day work week.

studentEssay:
Title: Imagine your life without the automobile. What would it be like?
In last June, I tripped Switzland just for travel. The airplane was so boring but it took me Switzland from South Korea in 13 hours. Thanks to it, I could travel for 14 days and spent just a day for moving countries.
In modern life, the automobile become one of most important things. we use cars, trams, trains, buses, ships, and airplanes. We often use it to get to work, trip the other cities or countries, and even for war or sports. Then what would be like if all automobiles suddenly disappeared?
At first, our work would become too unefficient. We cannot meet easily like before and contacting foreigners for business in offline become almost impossible. It is serious because we works with foreigners for a lot of times nowadays. For example, conference from various country can held 1 time or 2 times per a year because of old mobile like horses. This would causes the less improvement for science and math.
Second, the size of import and export would very smaller without the automobile, in modern life, we can eat beef from U.S. and coffee roasted with coffee bean in Africa. Without automobile, all we eat would be restricted and become more expensive. With import and export, countries could grow up by developing what they can make well and exchanging it.
Third, trip to other cities or countries would become impossible, If we don't have automobiles, we should spend at least 10 day to go to Busan from Daejeon. Furthermore, we can't even go China because of North Korea. Someone might think it is not neccessary but for some cities, trip is most earning parts among any other industries.
Automobile have some serious problems, Earth pollution, used in war, and some like that. However, we cannot even live 'modern life' without the automobile. We should find solutions for automobile's problems, not argueing we have to prohibit automobiles.
The automobile obviously improved countries, cities and indivisuals so far.

peerEssay:
Title: The Advantages of Having a Pet

Last winter, I have decided to adopt a cat from the shelter near my home. The cat was very playful and it brung me so many happy times. Pets can be an incredible part of our lives, offering company and support when we need it most.

In the modern world, pet become one of best companions for people. We can have cats, dogs, birds, and even reptiles. Pet is not only our friend but also can serve as a watch animal or therapy assistant. Then what would happen if everyone could have pet at home?

Firstly, having a pet is great for emotional wellbeing. They often cheer us up, especially dogs who love play and attention. It is scientifically proven that pet helps reduce stress and loneliness. Having dog or cat can turn sad day into happy time.

Second, pets can teach us a responsibility. Growing up with a pet mean you have learn to feed, clean, and care for another living being. It is a great lesson for children and adults alike. In some cases, pet can also be a safety measure, alerting owners in dangerous situations.

Third, pets create bond with their owners like no other. They never judge and always welcome you home. Someone might think pets are expensive but benefit they provide is worth. For instance, therapy dogs are crucial part for many people's lives.

Some people think pets make mess and hard to handle. However, the joy and companionship pets bring is irreplaceable. Therefore, instead of banning pets, we should finding ways to include them more positively into our lives.

Having a pet improve many aspects of life and enhance our happiness.

studentEssay:
Long time ago, people worked 6 days in one week in Korea. But after Korea became little strong country, people work 5 days in one week and many people think this decision was right. However, is it good to reduce working days 5 to 4 like the past? Of course 4-day work week will have both good and bad points. But in my opinion, I think 4-day work week should not be done because it has more disadventages than adventages.
 First, if we work only 4 days in one week, there will be more work in one day. Suppose that you have work to do in one week. It is very easy to think that there will be more work to do in one day if you do this work only 4 days, not 5 days. This is not good for you and company, too. It is because it can cause health problems or mental issue and also the quality of work will be down.
 Second, not working long time is not good. If we work only 4 days in week, that mean we don't work almost half of the week. In my opinion, this will decrease working ability. It is easy to forgot the things to do in working days and also it can affect quality or time, too. For example, if I study only 4 days in a week, my studing ability may decrease. I will forgot the things I learn while 3days that I don't study.
 In conclusion, I disagree that there should be a 4-day work week. It is because there will be more work in one day, so it will affect bad for individuals and companys and not working long time is not good.

Many people like drink coffee every morning. Coffee is favorite beverage for many people around world. But some people argue that coffee is not good for health. Is drinking coffee every day a good habit? In my opinion, I think coffee should not be drink too much because it have more negative sides than positive sides.
 First, if you drink coffee every day, you may become addicted. Suppose that you drink coffee every morning. It is very easy to see that you cannot start your day without coffee, if you do this every day. This is not healthy for body and mind, too. It is because it can cause sleep problems or anxiety issue and also your energy level will be down.
 Second, drinking coffee long time is not good. If you drink too much coffee, it mean your body get used to caffeine. This will decrease body's natural energy level. It is easy to forgot that natural way to boost energy like good sleep and healthy diet.
 In conclusion, I disagree that drinking coffee every day is a good habit. It is because it can make you addicted, so it will affect bad for your health and drinking coffee long time is not good.

studentEssay:
In these days, some people say there should be a 4-day work week. And new Kodea president also does similar project, 4.5-day work week. But, does it really efficient for our society? I think there should be many things to be considered.
First, isn't there loss to company? In country, there are a lot of companies, and there are also a lot of people who work in companies more than companies exist. People who say there should be a 4-day work week mainly say there will not be loss to companies because people with 4-day work week will work harder than 5-day work week. But 24-hour is not small time. Companies fight with another companies, and country's main industry fights with other country's companies. If we do 4-day work week project while other countries still do 5-day work week, we could lose our competitiveness.

studentEssay:
Do you know why the week takes 7 days? For a long time ago our acients believed that "7" is the perfect number of harmony. So they chose 7 days for one week. This is why we work 5 days a week and rest for 2 days. However, as time passes and people care about the effiency and work - life balance, some people suggested a 4-day work week which makes one week into 6 days. For this state, I disagree with this state for 2 reasons.
First of all, "Monday illness" will be worse. In Korea, every students and workers have "Monday illness", which they feel tired on Monsday after they rest for Saturday and Sunday. If there's a 4-day work week, we will rest more than a 5-day work week. Then, our tiredness and bothering will be worse.
Second, originally we spend 5 days for work in 7days. It means we work 5/7. If there was 4-day work week, then we work only 2/3. As we work less, the company will make a profit less. Then, we might work on Saturday or Sunday, too. Working on weekend make people feel much worse, so I disagree with 4-day work week.
In conclusion, I disagree with 4-day work week for worse of "Monday illness" and working weekend. If we try to change original system, we have to think deeply what this will cause.

peerEssay:
How do insects survive the winter? Many people wonders how these tiny creatures can endure the cold. Insects are very adaptable and have different strategies. Some species enter a state of very low activity called diapause. This allow them to survive the harsh conditions. This is why you rarely see insects during the months they are inactive. However, we do not fully understand how all insects handle the cold. More research is needed to discover more about insects winter habits.
First, some insects migrate to warm places. We can think of this like birds do. If insects can find a better place to live during winter, they will go. But not all insects migrate, only certain species do.
Second, insects have natural antifreeze in their bodies. When it is cold, this antifreeze stop their body fluids from freezing. This is another way they survive the winter surprisingly.
In conclusion, insects have many ways to handle winter. While some migrate, other uses chemicals in their bodies to stay alive. It is important to learn more about them to understand fully how they manage the season.

studentEssay:
In my opinion, 4-day work week is not good for us. There are three reasons.
First, if we take a rest three days a week, it is difficult to focus on working again. Anyone can think deep break time makes high work efficiency. However, I think two days are regular break time for coming back to working completely. 
Second, it can cause economic problems. Economies of country is moved by many companies. If we work only 4 days a week, regardless for working efficiency, income of company will decline exactly. Because 5 days that we can work for reduce to 4 days. Then, naturally income of country will reduce, and economy will be bad. It is a important problem to think about before talking about working efficiency.
Finally, sleeping patterns of employees can cause several problems. Original way that taking a rest for two days is so short that can't change sleeping patterns of employees. In weekend, we often watch TV late or drink late, then pattern breaks. In contrast, three days are enough to change sleeping pattern. So it can affect to working like take a nap while working.
Based on these three reasons. I think 4-day work week is not good.

In my view, remote education is bad for students. There are some reasons.

First, without attending schools in person, students feel unmotivated. Anyone can believe learning from home gives flexibility. However, I think classrooms offer regular motivation completely.

Second, it may cause issues with communication. Teachers and students are connecting through technology. If we rely only on remote education, regardless of its flexibility, interactions of students decline dramatically. Because the time spent face-to-face reduces significantly. Then, naturally, student morale will drop, and learning will suffer. It is a big concern to consider before promoting remote education.

Finally, study patterns of students can cause many disturbances. Original way of attending school keep students on track that can’t change students’ study habits abruptly. With online classes, we do often miss out on peer interactions then habits break. In contrast, traditional way keeps study pattern steady. So it can affect on learning like longer screen times.

Based on these three reasons. I think remote education is not good.

studentEssay: Recently, the number of people travelling abroad have increased. It is because there was the advance of transportation and economy. Many people want to go abroad for their own reasons. Then, should we study abroad for our future? I say, "No.". Even though there are many advantages of abroad studying, the choice must be determined carefully depending on your circumstance. So, you don't have to study abroad if it is not necessary for you. The most important thing is not abroad studying but yourself studying hard.

studentEssay:
Nowadays, there are the discussions about the 4-day work week. Some people say 4-day work week improves the efficiency of the work, but the other say it won't work because of several reasons. In my opinion, there shouldn't be a 4-day work week. Let's talk about some reasons on my opinion.
 First, the total amount of work may decrease if 4-day work week is conducted. This causes decrease of domestic production and national competitiveness.
 Second, people try to rest somehow. The word 'work-life balance' appear recently. It means that people need to balance between work and life. In other words, people already know how to rest while they work.
 Third, there is no evidence that 4-day work week improves the efficiency of the work. To rest is very important, but many rests make people lazy. So, there is no correlation between 4-day work week and improvement of the work performance.

 First, the total amount of work may decrease if 4-day work week is conducted. This causes decrease of domestic production and national competitiveness.
 Second, people try to rest somehow. The word 'work-life balance' appear recently. It means that people need to balance between work and life. In other words, people already know how to rest while they work.
 Third, there is no evidence that 4-day work week improves the efficiency of the work. To rest is very important, but many rests make people lazy. So, there is no correlation between 4-day work week and improvement of the work performance. 
 There are several reasons why there shouldn't be a 4-day work week. The total work amount decreases, people already try to rest, there is no evidence about the improvement of the work performance, etc. So, there shouldn't be a 4-day work week.

TITLE: There should be a 4-day work week.

Many foreign workers in Korea have a difficulty in something. Can you guess what it is? It’s working hour (time). They usually have had hard time to adopt Korea working system. Korea works too much. Even though it decreased than before, the A of Korean work up to 55 hours per week. So, today, I’ll discuss why There should be a 4-day work week. Now, I’ll give you more details.

To begin with, we can do more in work if we get relax more. Think about When you take over the night studying. Was the efficiency good? Maybe not. It’s same as workers. They should get relax more, take a sleep and then come to work place with high quality of energy and condition.

Secondly, if there is a 4-day work week, the increasing of spending would be expected. Spending could be a good for economics. Many can cycle and small marketers can sell more things. For example, Past in Korea, when it changed to 5-day work week from 6-day work week, Many people worried that workers efficiency will get down. However, people spend a lot of time and Money so the economics could be circulated.

Lastly, it can be welfare to workers time take off one day. They do not need to use their personal holiday to their work place. Everybody get a break. So, people can live more happily.

Then, how to make it for real? I’ll suggest some ways to bring it.
First way: work free on wednesday. If we take a break on wednesday, we only work two days directly. Wednesday is profit for holiday because it located middle of weeks days.
Second way: replace work free days zig-zag. For example, people whose birth-year ends with 0,5 → Mon, 1,6 → Tue, 2,7 → Wednesday, 3,8 → Thur, 4,9 → Fri work free.

TITLE: The Importance of Reducing Plastic Waste.

Many communities around the world have a serious issue in something. Can you guess what it is? It’s waste plastic. They usually are have hard time to handle the problem. The world use too much plastic. Even though some countries have taken steps, the amount of plastic waste continues to rising every year. So, today, I’ll discuss why we need to reduce plastic waste. Now, I’ll give you more details.

First, reducing plastic waste can help protect wildlife. Think about When you see picture of animals trapped in plastic. Was the impact good? Definitely not. Animals should have environment free from plastic, so they can live without harm and disruption.

Secondly, people would benefit from cleaner environments if less plastic used. Cleaner areas could attract tourists, which is good for economics. For example, Some regions, when they cleaned up beaches from plastics, seen an increase in tourism revenue. Therefore, reducing plastic can support economic growth.

Lastly, it can improve healthcare systems. Waste plastics can cause serious health risk over time. Everybody benefit from cleaner environments, so communities can become more healthy places.

Then, how to achieve this? I’ll suggest some ways to reduce plastic effectively.
First way: promote reusable products in markets. If markets adopt eco-friendly policies, we can cut down on plastic usage significantly.
Second way: implement stronger regulations on plastic production. For example, governments whose policies restrict plastic usage can see significant waste reduction.

revised_essay:
Today, people have different needs, so there are many types of work. In Korea, most companies follow a 5-day work week, but many people want a 4-day work week. I think there are many benefits to a 4-day work week.

First, work-life balance has become much more important than in the past. Money is also important, but spending time with family, resting, and having time for personal development are even more valuable these days. Having only two days of personal time per week is not enough.

Second, efficiency is more important than spending long hours at work. I think concentrating for a short time and achieving the best results is the most effective way to work. In Europe, some companies have already adopted a 4-day work week because they believe efficiency is the most important factor.

Third, companies can hire more employees. With a 4-day work week, each person may earn slightly less, allowing companies to employ more people. More employees bring diverse ideas, which can help the company develop and innovate.

In conclusion, considering people’s needs and company development, a 4-day work week is a better choice.

studentEssay:
Some people say that "5-day work week is too ling and 2-day weekend is too short". So, they argue that we need to change 5-day work week to 4-day work week. This opinion has lots of advantage and most people also want 4-day work week. But, I think this opinion has more disadvantage. So I disagree there should be 4-day work week.

First reason that I disagree is if there is 4-day work week, we need more work on week. When 5-day work week changes 4-day work week, if we work same amount, result amount will decrease. So, we work more harder to fill decreased amount and this will lead to harder work in work week.

Second reason is we already have much time to spend our hobby time. Some people who agree 4-day work week argue that if we change work week, we spend enough time to enjoy hobby. But I think we already have enough time to spend our hobby time. Because when we rest on weekend, we consume enough time to exercise, watch movie, and so on. Moreover, we also have free time on work week when we finish the work.

For this reason, I think that we don’t have to change 5-day work week to 4-day work week. 5-day work week also has many free time and didn’t need harder work.

Many people believe that exercise is very important for health, but some people do not think it is necessary. Exercise have many health benefits like reducing stress and better sleep. However, I think there is also more concern about exercise.

First reason why I think so is the risk of injury. When people exercise too much, they can hurt their body. For example, running too long might cause knee pain or leg injury. If they injured, it can take time to recover, and it will not be good for health.

Second reason is time consumption. Some people say exercising requires much free time every day. But they already spend enough time working, and relaxation. People also need spend time with family and friends in weekend. Balance between work and rest time is important.

For these reasons, exercise can be helpful, but it not only solution for good health. It's about finding right balance in daily life.

studentEssay:
Title: Imagine your life without the automobile. What would it be like?
In last June, I tripped Switzland just for travel. The airplane was so boring but it took me Switzland from South Korea in 13 hours. Thanks to it, I could travel for 14 days and spent just a day for moving countries.
In modern life, the automobile become one of most important things. We use cars, trams, trains, buses, ships, and airplanes. We often use it to get to work, trip the other cities or countries, and even for war or sports. Then what would be like if all automobiles suddenly disappeared?
At first, our work would become too inefficient. We cannot meet easily like before and contacting foreigners for business in offline become almost impossible. It is serious because we works with foreigners a lot of times nowadays. For example, conference from various country can be held 1 time or 2 times per a year because of old mobile like horses. This would causes the less improvement for science and math.
Second, the size of import and export would very smaller without the automobile. In modern life, we can eat beef from U.S. and coffee roasted with coffee bean in Africa. Without automobile, all we eat would be restricted and become more expensive. With import and export, countries could grow up by developing what they can make well and exchanging it.
Third, trip to other cities or countries would become impossible. If we don't have automobiles, we should spend at least 10 day to go to Busan from Daejeon. Furthermore, we can't even go China because of North Korea. Someone might think it is not necessary but for some cities, trip is most earning parts among any other industries.
Automobile have some serious problems. Earth pollution, used in war, and some like that. However, we cannot even live 'modern life' without the automobile. We should find solutions for automobile's problems, not arguing we have to prohibit automobiles.
The automobile obviously improved countries, cities and individuals so far.

revised_essay:
Title: Imagine your life without the automobile. What would it be like?
In last June, I tripped Switzland just for travel. The airplane was so boring but it took me Switzland from South Korea in 13 hours. Thanks to it, I could travel for 14 days and spent just a day for moving countries.
In modern life, the automobile become one of most important things. We use cars, trams, trains, buses, ships, and airplanes. We often use it to get to work, trip the other cities or countries, and even for war or sports. Then what would be like if all automobiles suddenly disappeared?
At first, our work would become too inefficient. We cannot meet easily like before and contacting foreigners for business in offline become almost impossible. It is serious because we works with foreigners a lot of times nowadays. For example, conference from various country can be held 1 time or 2 times per a year because of old mobile like horses. This would causes the less improvement for science and math.
Second, the size of import and export would very smaller without the automobile. In modern life, we can eat beef from U.S. and coffee roasted with coffee bean in Africa. Without automobile, all we eat would be restricted and become more expensive. With import and export, countries could grow up by developing what they can make well and exchanging it.
Third, trip to other cities or countries would become impossible. If we don't have automobiles, we should spend at least 10 day to go to Busan from Daejeon. Furthermore, we can't even go China because of North Korea. Someone might think it is not necessary but for some cities, trip is most earning parts among any other industries.
Automobile have some serious problems. Earth pollution, used in war, and some like that. However, we cannot even live 'modern life' without the automobile. We should find solutions for automobile's problems, not arguing we have to prohibit automobiles.
The automobile obviously improved countries, cities and individuals so far.
peerEssay:
Save money is not only about reduce expenses. It involves planning and managing your funds wisely. Many people think that saving begins with stop spending money on entertainments but this is not the only way.

First, making budget can really help you. It helps you track where your money are going and how much you are spending. Contrary to buying things without care, budgeting allows you to plan your expense.

Second, you should think about invest in stocks or mutual funds. Simple saving is good, but invest can increase your money over time. However, it is important to know risks are involved. You need to research about investment options.

Thirdly, avoid to buy expensive items if they are not urgent. Luxury products often will cost you lots of money. Think if you really need them or if there's a affordable alternative.

Lastly, emergencies fund is critical. Life is unpredictable, and having saving for unforeseen events like car repair or health problems is wise. Without this, a expensive bill can ruin your financial plan easily.

In conclusion, saving money is not just about cutting down your shopping. It's about creating a balance between spending and saving, planning well, and preparing for unexpected cost. Saving effectively is crucial for a stable financial future, and anyone can achieve this by little awareness and effort.
