studentEssay:
Many university students consider whether they have to study abroad. Some students apply being exchange students, other students study in only their countries. In my opinion, I think that students should study abroad. Let me explain three reasons.
 First of all, students can experience various views. For example, in France, mathematics is based on logic which France has only. Therefore, if students study in country which has it's own advantages in students' interested field, they can experience various views. 
 Second, students can learn from famous professor. For example, in other country, there are Dokinson, Karl Seigon, Michael Sandel, who are famous people in their fields. However, there are few chances to meet them in students' countries. Therefore, if students study in countries which have famous professor, they can learn many things.
 Lastly, students can take part in a symposium of subject in which they are interested. There are many symposiums of various subjects in other countries. Students can share their papers, review other's papers, and communicate their opinions and feedbacks. So, if students take part in a symposium in other countries, they can improve their research skills.
 For these reasons, I think that students should study abroad. It will make students experience various views, learn from famous professors, take part in a symposium of subject in which they are interested.

studentEssay:
Have you heard about the case genius students go abroad and study there?
Maybe Harvard, MIT and Oxford and so on… Many good universities are the symbol of being good at studying for Korean students.
But I think for students to study abroad is not necessary.
First, we are living in Korea, which has many good universities such as SNU, KAIST and Yonsei. There are many professors who studied in abroad universities, so they can make students have various perspectives. So those who want to study under good professors can study in Korea.
Second, we are living in the 21st century. It makes students meet and talk to others online. The benefits of studying abroad are the opportunities to meet someone different from us, to share opinions. But nowadays, technology enables us to do those things.
To sum up, studying abroad for students is not vital. Even though studying abroad is beneficial, it is okay to study in our country. The growth of domestic universities and technology can make students study over the boundary of country.

studentEssay:
Can't we just work 4days per week?
Yes we can't. I firmly believe that we have to work 5 days per week. There are two main reasons about it : Economic depression and society problems. Let's go deeply about these. 
The first main reason is Economic depression. Economic system will be damaged in many ways if we change into 4-day work. For example, companies will lose their efficiency of producing, and many people will lose their job. And it will leaded to economic depression.
The second main reason is about laws and society problems. Since many laws are fitted to 5-day working, the change must involve a change of laws too. During the law-changing days, people may feel confused. And it can be leaded to some society problems such as sabotage.
For these reasons, we can't work only 4 days per week. Maybe 4-day working is great, but our society is not ready to accept such a big change. 
Thank you for reading.

peerEssay: Do you think that social media has many effects on people lives? I think it has both good and bad sides. First, certain social media platform connect people who live in different location and background. For example, we can meet friends from other countries through social media group or online classes. We engage with peoples cultures and learn new language from these networks. And social platforms make easy to share photos and video with large group of people. Second, I feel the influence of social media on my emotions. When I read stories or news from social media, I can feel happy or sad. Many people including me gets different feelings through posts and this make them more connected. It is like a window to another world where I can feel excitement or disappointment quickly. We gain experience not only in the present but also from historical and futuristic stories shared. Finally, social media informs about recent trend about fashion and technology. I often see advertisement and use those ideas while shopping. News feeds on social media tell about current events or political matters from diverse place. Social media influence human interaction significantly. It shows us global interactions and shares diverse personal experience. For these reasons, I propose social platforms have many impacts on society.

studentEssay:
TITLE: Don't need a A day wont week
I think a four-day work week is not needed. Firstly, it will not only be unhelpful but also make the situation worse. With a longer weekend, the free time will increase, but the amount of work that a company should complete in a month does not change. Therefore, we must complete the same amount of work in a shorter period. It causes many health problems, border working life, and a lot of working at night. Eventually, a four-day work week cannot achieve its goal of making life better by providing a longer weekend.

Second, there can be many opinions that support a five-day work and two-day weekend system. It has already become a social standard. Every school and college follows that rule. But if students go to school only four days a week, it will reduce learning and cause the loss of many genius students who could lead a country.

Third, harder work brings many health problems. I wrote a short essay, but it is a very important problem. The worst problem is a lack of sleep. Experts suggest people sleep 8 hours a day, but we already cannot follow that. It may hurt more than before, and many will sleep under 5 hours in a day. A lack of sleep destroys our immune system and leads to a higher chance of many diseases, including cancer. Some may say that we can sleep more in the 3-day rest, but it will make the situation worse. We should sleep in balance.

studentEssay:
Do you know why the week takes 7 days? For a long time ago our acients believed that "7" is the perfect number of harmony. So they chose 7 days for one week. This is why we work 5 days a week and rest for 2 days. However, as time passes and people care about the efficiency and work - life balance, some people suggested 4-day work week which makes one week into 6 days. For this state, I disagree with this state for 2 reasons.
First of all, "Monday illness" will be worse. In Korea, every students and workers have "Monday illness", which they feel tired on Monday after they rest for Saturday and Sunday. If there's 4-day work week, we will rest more than 5-day work week. Then, our tiredness and bothering will be worse.
Second, originally we spend 5 days for work in 7 days. It means we work 5/7. If there was 4-day work week, then we work only 2/3. As we work less, the company will make a profit less. Then, we might work on Saturday or Sunday to protect the risk of company. Working on weekend makes people feel much worse, so I disagree with 4-day work week.
In conclusion, I disagree with 4-day work week for worse of "Monday illness" and working weekend. If we try to change original system, we have to think deeply what this will affects to our life.

peerEssay:
Do you ever wonder why the traffic is so crowded? For a long period ago, our townspeople did not use cars; they walked everywhere. That is why roads were less occupied and people could walk freely. But as time goes and people begin to prefer convenience, they start to use more cars to travel short distances. For this situation, I disagree with this situation for 2 reasons.

First of all, road rage will be increased. In my city, every drivers and cyclists experiences road rage, which makes them irritated and angry while traveling. If there's a more cars on the road, traffic will be more congested. Then, our stress and aggression will become worse.

Second, originally there were less pollution when less cars existed. It means air was cleaner and environment was healthier. If more people use cars frequently, air quality becomes worse. Then, we might face more environmental problems due to car emissions. These problems make people feel worried, so I am not agreeing with more car usage.

In conclusion, I disagree with more cars usage due to increased road rage and pollution. If we try to change original habits, we have to think thoroughly what these will impact to our future.

revised_essay:
TITLE: We Don't Need a Four-Day Work Week

I believe that a four-day work week is unnecessary. Not only would it be unhelpful, but it could actually make the situation worse. Although having a longer weekend may seem attractive, the total amount of work a company must complete in a month does not change. This means employees would be forced to finish the same amount of work in a shorter period. As a result, they would face more stress, irregular working hours, and more late-night work. Eventually, a four-day work week would fail to achieve its goal of improving people’s lives.

Secondly, the current five-day work and two-day weekend system is already well established as a social standard. Schools and universities follow this schedule as well. If students attended school only four days a week, it would reduce learning time and possibly result in the loss of talented individuals who could become future leaders.

Lastly, more intense working days could lead to serious health issues. The biggest problem is lack of sleep. Experts recommend eight hours of sleep per day, but many people already fail to meet that standard. With a compressed work schedule, people may end up sleeping less than five hours a day. Chronic sleep deprivation weakens the immune system and increases the risk of various diseases, including cancer. Some might argue that people can catch up on sleep during a three-day weekend, but irregular sleep patterns only make things worse. A healthy life requires balance, not extremes.
peerEssay:
TITLE: Internet is not all ways useful
We do not need the internet all the times. First, it will create more problems than solutions. Internet can provide quick answers, its also might make us lazy to think deeper. Our critical thinking skills may reduce because we depend too much on searching informations easily, rather than solving problems on our own. Thus, increasing internet uses can harm our mental abilities.

Second, losing real social interactions can occur more if we rely on internet. Many people think that internet help us connect better, but it actually increases feelings of isolation. If we continue this path, people will lose real emotion and chance to build genuine relationships with others.

Third, there are many negative effects on health due to internet use. I will give one point here, which is a major concern for health. Longer screen time leads to eyesight issues. We already have difficulties in reducing screen time, to add more will only worsen eyesight, and makes our health deteriorate. It can result in more numbers of people needing eye care services. Solitude cannot be replaced by virtual interactions, so we need balance.

studentEssay:
Have you heard about cases where genius students go abroad to study?
Maybe Harvard, MIT, Oxford and so on… Many good universities are considered symbols of academic excellence for Korean students.
But I think it is not necessary for students to study abroad.
First, we are living in Korea, which has many good universities such as SNU, KAIST, and Yonsei. There are many professors who studied at foreign universities, so they can give students various perspectives. Therefore, those who want to study under good professors can do so in Korea.
Second, we are living in the 21st century. It allows students to meet and talk to others online. The benefits of studying abroad are the opportunities to meet people different from us and to share opinions. But nowadays, technology enables us to do those things as well.
To sum up, studying abroad is not vital for students. Even though studying abroad is beneficial, it is fine to study in our own country. The growth of domestic universities and technology can help students study beyond the boundaries of the country.

revised_essay:
Have you heard about cases where talented students go abroad to study?
Perhaps to Harvard, MIT, Oxford, and other prestigious universities. For many Korean students, such schools are seen as symbols of academic excellence.

However, I believe it is not necessary for students to study abroad.

First, Korea already has many excellent universities such as SNU, KAIST, and Yonsei. Many professors here have studied overseas, so they can provide students with diverse perspectives. Therefore, those who want to learn from outstanding professors can do so without leaving Korea.

Second, we are living in the 21st century, a time when students can meet and interact with others online. The main benefit of studying abroad is the opportunity to meet people from different backgrounds and share ideas, but today’s technology already makes this possible.

In conclusion, studying abroad is not essential for students. Although it has benefits, studying in our own country is also a valuable option. The development of domestic universities and advanced technology allows students to gain knowledge beyond national boundaries.

revised_essay:
I think visual media negatively influences people's behavior. Visual media does not have a high degree of regulation for harmful content and provides fewer educational resources. As a result, children who have not yet developed independent thinking and self-control may assume that what they see in visual media is acceptable in society and imitate those behaviors.

Some people argue that visual media also contains educational videos, books, or other useful resources. However, children’s and even adults’ brains tend to prefer media content that stimulates dopamine release. Consequently, people are naturally drawn away from educational content. Watching visual media from an early age is not beneficial for children. Whether the content is educational or not, it reduces their ability to focus for long periods because of flashing lights and rapid scene changes. Over time, the brain becomes weaker at concentrating on a single task. If this continues, children may lose the ability to read books or study for hours and may struggle to engage in meaningful conversations with others.

On the positive side, visual media allows people to make friends, share memes, and create new content. It connects people globally and provides entertainment for social interactions. However, in Korea these days, there are also negative side effects. Trends change very quickly, and memes do not last long. This creates disconnection among young people, since they cannot always share the same topics. In some elementary schools, bullying has occurred: children exclude peers who are unfamiliar with current memes, leaving them isolated.

Although visual media has positive effects, I believe these benefits can also be achieved through reading books or studying. In contrast, the negative effects seem to outweigh the positive ones. Therefore, I think visual media influences people’s behavior negatively.

studentEssay:
Now, I'll write my thought about the criteria of a good roommate. I spent Spring and Summer Semester in KAIST, and start fall semester few days ago. I'll demonstrate following statement based on these three different expirences. 
    Freshmen in KAIST belong to a group by randomly, I have good relationship in my group. But unfortunately, my dorm roommates were other group. Moreover, both are not close, so mood in our room was very awkward. I tried to be closer with 2 roommates, but I failed. Time flies, and I couldn't request my opinion because our relationship was so far that I can't even tell them anything. They turn on the light at very late night, do not tidy up, ear ramen in my room and even do not refresh air like opening window. It was very stressful. So, I think good roommate is a person who turn off the light at late night and bring standing ligth by ownselves, who tidy up room regularly and open the window if he eats something in my room.
    Next, I'll write about my Summer. In Summer, I could choose close friend. Also it was 2 men in 1 room. So, I was so happy because I thought I escape the hell. But, there was small problem. Everyday my friend ask me to play PC game and I play with him. It is good for a moment, but when I recall my Summer it is very regretful. I'm just thinking that I wasted my time. For this reason, good roommate is a person who give me positive effect to my life pattern.
    Lastly, in Fall semester, I get my roommates who are close with me. I was glad. But there is a problem. Because we are too close, they do not respect my time. I want to sleep, but they don't care about me and talking each other. So, good roommate is a person who respect my time although we are friend.
    To sum up, I write criteria of good roommate based on my experience. First, person who turn off the light at late night and bring own standing light. Second, person who tidy up room regularly. Third, person who open the door if he eats something. Fourth, person who help my life healthy and efficient. In last, person who respect my time. These five things are qualities of good roommate I think. Thank you

I'll demonstrate following thoughts based on these different expirences. Sometimes, people say books are not necessary in modern world, but I disagree with that opinion. Reading is important because it enhance our knowledge, increases vocabulary and help to improve concentration. 

Firstly, books give us much information about world. They provide knowledge that can help us understand complex ideas and concepts. It is true that internet has lot information, but book provides a depth knowledge that online can't match. So, reading is a way to increase understanding about variety subjects. 

Secondly, the more we read, the more words we can add to our vocabulary. Reading allows us to see how words are used in context and it is a good way to learn new words. This is important because it help us to express ourselves better in both written and spoken language. 

Moreover, reading books require concentration, which is beneficial for our brain. When we read, we need to pay attention to understand story or information. It can be a challenge at first, but over time, it becomes easier to focus for longer periods. This can improve our ability to concentrate in other areas of life too. 

To sum up, I write the benefits of reading books based on my expirences. First, it gives us wide knowledge. Second, it increase our vocabulary. Third, it improve our concentration. From my point of view, these are the reasons why reading is important in our life. Thank you.

These five factors are key features of balanced diet I think. Thank you

studentEssay:
Nowadays, there are the discussions about the 4-day work week. Some people say 4-day work week improves the efficiency of the work, but the other say it won't work because of several reasons. In my opinion, there shouldn't be a 4-day work week. Let's talk about some reasons on my opinion.
 First, the total amount of work may decrease if 4-day work week is conducted. This causes decrease of domestic production and national competitiveness.
 Second, people try to rest somehow. The word 'work-life balance' appear recently. It means that people need to balance between work and life. In other words, people already know how to rest while they work.
 Third, there is no evidence that 4-day work week improves the efficiency of the work. To rest is very important, but many rests make people lazy. So, there is no correlation between 4-day work week and improvement of the work performance. 
 There are several reasons why there shouldn't be a 4-day work week. The total work amount decreases, people already try to rest, there is no evidence about the improvement of the work performance, etc. So, there shouldn't be a 4-day work week.

studentEssay:
Long time ago, people worked 6 days in one week in Korea. But after Korea became little strong country, people work 5 days in one week and many people think this decision was right. However, reducing working days 5 to 4 like the past is not good. Of course 4-day work week will have both good and bad points. But, 4-day work week should not be done because it has more disadventages than adventages.
 First, if we work only 4 days in one week, there will be more work in one day. Suppose that you have work to do in one week. It is very easy to think that there will be more work to do in one day if you do this work only 4 days, not 5 days. This is not good for you and company, too. It is because it can cause health problems or mental issue and also the quality of work will be down.
 Second, not working long time is not good. If we work only 4 days in week, that mean we don't work almost half of the week. This will decrease working ability. It is easy to forgot the things to do in working days and also it can affect quality or time, too. For example, if I study only 4 days in a week, my studing ability may decrease. I will forgot the things I learn while 3days that I don't study.
 In conclusion, I disagree that there should be a 4-day work week. It is because there will be more work in one day, so it will affect bad for individuals and companys and not working long time is not good.

studentEssay:
Many people who incloud my parent and friends want to do 4-day work week and get 3-day weekend. Sometime I would want that, too when I felt tired because of busy weekday. However, I don't agree that we have to get 4 day work on a week. There are two reasons why I don't agree that.
First reason is that we are more busy and tired in weekday if we do 4-day work. Many people who want it think that if 4-day work is accepted, their work time is reduced, so it is more free than before. But, in fact, the amount of 4-day work in a week is similar with before 5-day work in a week. It makes to increase the density of weekday and us be felt tired and busy. In my case, I felt more busy and difficult when I tried to finish my homework for getting more free time.
Finally, I think that we will be felt hard to return weekday if a length of weekend is incresed. I have seen that almost people felt more hard when they got much holiday than weekend. In my case, The size of my thoughts which I don’t want to return classes is bigger in weekend than in vacation.
A 4-day work week is looked like reducing our work and giving us relax, but it gives us increasing density of work time and more tired. So, I think we have to do 5-day work week.

That makes we can receive whatever we want within only few days, over the mountains, rivers, and seas.

Improving logistics is also good for technological improvement. we can transfer information and material efficiency. Hand-carry have so many weakness to protect their cargo. but nowadays we can protect carefully with the automobile. U.S. president can survive at nuclear bomb within his own car.

Automobile gives us safe environment such as closed, private space when moving. In past, so many people are died by cold or hot weather, animal like tiger, etc. But we can survive nowadays at this situation by only following safety instructions.

Moving is huge part of logistics and our life. Walking and running are the most inefficient ways to transport. So automobile improves huge part of our modern life.

studentEssay:
I think visual media negatively influences people's behavior. Visual media does not have a high degree of regulation for harmful content and provides fewer educational resources. As a result, children who have not yet developed independent thinking and self-control may assume that what they see in visual media is acceptable in society and imitate those behaviors.

Some people argue that visual media also contains educational videos, books, or other useful resources. However, children’s and even adults’ brains tend to prefer media content that stimulates dopamine release. Consequently, people are naturally drawn away from educational content. Watching visual media from an early age is not beneficial for children. Whether the content is educational or not, it reduces their ability to focus for long periods because of flashing lights and rapid scene changes. Over time, the brain becomes weaker at concentrating on a single task. If this continues, children may lose the ability to read books or study for hours and may struggle to engage in meaningful conversations with others.

On the positive side, visual media allows people to make friends, share memes, and create new content. It connects people globally and provides entertainment for social interactions. However, in Korea these days, there are also negative side effects. Trends change very quickly, and memes do not last long. This creates disconnection among young people, since they cannot always share the same topics. In some elementary schools, bullying has occurred: children exclude peers who are unfamiliar with current memes, leaving them isolated.

Although visual media has positive effects, I believe these benefits can also be achieved through reading books or studying. In contrast, the negative effects seem to outweigh the positive ones. Therefore, I think visual media influences people’s behavior negatively.

Some people argue that visual media also contains educational videos, books, or other useful resources. However, children’s and even adults’ brains tend to prefer media content that stimulates dopamine release. Consequently, people are naturally drawn away from educational content. Watching visual media from an early age is not beneficial for children. Whether the content is educational or not, it reduces their ability to focus for long periods because of flashing lights and rapid scene changes. Over time, the brain becomes weaker at concentrating on a single task. If this continues, children may lose the ability to read books or study for hours and may struggle to engage in meaningful conversations with others.

On the positive side, visual media allows people to make friends, share memes, and create new content. It connects people globally and provides entertainment for social interactions. However, in Korea these days, there are also negative side effects. Trends change very quickly, and memes do not last long. This creates disconnection among young people, since they cannot always share the same topics. In some elementary schools, bullying has occurred: children exclude peers who are unfamiliar with current memes, leaving them isolated.

Although visual media has positive effects, I believe these benefits can also be achieved through reading books or studying. In contrast, the negative effects seem to outweigh the positive ones. Therefore, I think visual media influences people’s behavior negatively.
peerEssay:
Learning foreign languages has both positive and negative effects on people. Language learning can seem beneficial at first, providing access to different cultures and enhancing cognitive skills. Yet, it can come with challenges and misconceptions. Therefore, people may become frustrated with progress and feel less motivated.

While some advocate that learning a new language opens up career opportunities and improves communication with diverse populations. People also point out that the time investment is substantial. Additionally, not everyone has the environment to practice regularly, which makes the process less effective. Thus, it is difficult to achieve fluency without immersion.

At the same time, language education enables cultural exchanges and broadens understanding of worldviews. However, English, for instance, is often prioritized over other languages. In some contexts, it leads to cultural homogenization rather than valuing linguistic diversity. Moreover, focusing on English can create a gap between speakers of less common languages and those with global tongues.

Even though learning languages yields global awareness, it is essential to recognize the challenges along the way. The benefits of multilingualism are clear, but it is not without its difficulties. One needs genuine interest and the right resources to truly succeed.

However, it is not happy for me to hear that because I think that visual media influences people's behavior negatively. Why I think like that? Let me explain more.

Then he said like Youtubers. His tone and words got rough, and he easily lost his anger while just normal dialog. Comparing the time when he said more softly, I found that the difference was the time he watched Youtube. In addition, given that teenagers are said not to be able to communicate well, visual media is likely to has to do with negative behavior.
Second, visual media seeks profit, so it easily uses extreme action. For example, in Korean manner, it is not polite to eat noodle generating big sound. However, comedians eat noodle generating big sound to interest people and highlight how deliciously they could eat. After that, people more eat noodle with big sound. So, I think visual media spread impolite manners.
Third, more time we spend watching visual media, more our brain get tired. Then we cannot focus on our main work, easily make mistakes, more think negatively. It can influence the region of brain which controls behavior and other except visual sense, negatively. I watched negative behavior due to visual media, and I mentioned ones of that experiences in the previous paragraph. Visual media's influence is not so good, so we need to give effort to use it properly and not too much.

studentEssay:
Now, I'll write my thought about the criteria of a good roommate. I spent Spring and Summer Semester in KAIST, and start fall semester few days ago. I'll demonstrate following statement based on these three different experiences. 
    Freshmen in KAIST belong to a group by randomly, I have good relationship in my group. But unfortunately, my dorm roommates were other group. Moreover, both are not close, so mood in our room was very awkward. I tried to be closer with 2 roommates, but I failed. Time flies, and I couldn't request my opinion because our relationship was so far that I can't even tell them anything. They turn on the light at very late night, do not tidy up, ear ramen in my room and even do not refresh air like opening window. It was very stressful. So, I think good roommate is a person who turn off the light at late night and bring standing light by ourselves, who tidy up room regularly and open the window if he eats something in my room.
    Next, I'll write about my Summer. In Summer, I could choose close friend. Also it was 2 men in 1 room. So, I was so happy because I thought I escape the hell. But, there was small problem. Everyday my friend ask me to play PC game and I play with him. It is good for a moment, but when I recall my Summer it is very regretful. I'm just thinking that I wasted my time. For this reason, good roommate is a person who give me positive effect to my life pattern.
    Lastly, in Fall semester, I get my roommates who are close with me. I was glad. But there is a problem. Because we are too close, they do not respect my time. I want to sleep, but they don't care about me and talking each other. So, good roommate is a person who respect my time although we are friend.
    To sum up, I wrote criteria of good roommate based on my experience. First, person who turns off the light at late night and bring own standing light. Second, person who tidies up room regularly. Third, person who opens the door if he eats something. Fourth, person who helps my life healthy and efficient. In last, person who respects my time. These five things are qualities of good roommate I think. Thank you

peerEssay:
Now, I think about the qualities of a great teacher. Last year, I was in high school and this fall semester I start university. I'll describe my opinion based on these two different experiences. 

    Students in the school are assigned to classes randomly, and I have had good teachers. But, unfortunately, my math teacher was not very helpful. Moreover, both of us did not communicate, so the atmosphere in class was uncomfortable. I tried to ask questions, but I did not understand. Time fly, and I didn't have the chance to share my thoughts because the relationship was too distant and I can’t ask anything. They explain topics very briefly, do not provide examples, give tests too frequently and do not use interesting materials. It was very difficult. So, I think a great teacher is someone who explains well, use examples, provide clear homework, and finds ways to make the class interesting.

    Next, I'll write about my university experience. At university, we have more freedom to choose professors. I was hopeful because I could select who I wanted to learn from. But there are big problems. Everyday we have long lectures and I struggle to keep focus. It’s fine for a while, but when reflecting on my day, it is exhausting. Therefore, a great teacher understands students' capacity and makes learning comfortable. 

    Lastly, my favorite subject is history and I appreciate my professor. We have classes twice a week and it’s fascinating, however, it can still get hard. Because of deep topics, discussions are intense and require much from us. So, a great teacher balances challenge with engagement, even if the subject is tough.

    To conclude, I wrote about what makes a teacher great from my perspective. First, someone who clearly explains topics. Second, someone who provides engaging material. Third, someone who is considerate of student capacity. Fourth, someone who manages class discussions well. Lastly, someone who knows how to balance challenge and ease. These are my ideas of a great teacher. Thank you.

studentEssay:
Long time ago, people worked 6 days in one week in Korea. But after Korea became little strong country, people work 5 days in one week and many people think this decision was right. However, reducing working days 5 to 4 like the past is not good. Therefore 4-day work week should not be done because it has more disadventages than adventages.
 First, if we work only 4 days in one week, there will be more work in one day. Suppose that you have work to do in one week. It is very easy to think that there will be more work to do in one day if you do this work only 4 days, not 5 days. This is not good for you and company, too. It is because it can cause health problems or mental issue and also the quality of work will be down.
 Second, not working long time is not good. If we work only 4 days in week, that mean we don't work almost half of the week. This will decrease working ability. It is easy to forgot the things to do in working days and also it can affect quality or time, too. For example, if I study only 4 days in a week, my studing ability may decrease. I will forgot the things I learn while 3days that I don't study.
 In conclusion, I disagree that there should be a 4-day work week. It is because there will be more work in one day, so it will affect bad for individuals and companys and not working long time is not good.

peerEssay: Walking in the woods can be a good way for relax. Many people need a rest from busy daily lives. But going to the woods without knowing much information about it is not really a idea. When going to the forest, you need to carry some important items. This help to ensure you will have a safe journey and will be able to find your way back. First, it is important to bring enough water for the trip. Without water, it is easy to get dehydrated, especially if the weather is hot. Dehydration can cause serious health problem, so always have a steady supply. Second, don’t forget map. You cannot rely only on mobile devices which can lose battery or signal. A paper map is reliable and will guide you through paths. It is easy to forgot the way, and you might get lost if there is no map. It ensures your safety and makes sure you can return home safely. In conclusion, before going to the woods, remember to bring all essentials you need. It is because having a safe trip is important.

revised_essay:
I think visual media negatively influences people's behavior. Visual media does not have a high degree of regulation for harmful content and provides fewer educational resources. As a result, children who have not yet developed independent thinking and self-control may assume that what they see in visual media is acceptable in society and imitate those behaviors.

Some people argue that visual media also contains educational videos, books, or other useful resources. However, children’s and even adults’ brains tend to prefer media content that stimulates dopamine release. Consequently, people are naturally drawn away from educational content. Watching visual media from an early age is not beneficial for children. Whether the content is educational or not, it reduces their ability to focus for long periods because of flashing lights and rapid scene changes. Over time, the brain becomes weaker at concentrating on a single task. If this continues, children may lose the ability to read books or study for hours and may struggle to engage in meaningful conversations with others.

On the positive side, visual media allows people to make friends, share memes, and create new content. It connects people globally and provides entertainment for social interactions. However, in Korea these days, there are also negative side effects. Trends change very quickly, and memes do not last long. This creates disconnection among young people, since they cannot always share the same topics. In some elementary schools, bullying has occurred: children exclude peers who are unfamiliar with current memes, leaving them isolated.

Although visual media has positive effects, I believe these benefits can also be achieved through reading books or studying. In contrast, the negative effects seem to outweigh the positive ones. Therefore, I think visual media influences people’s behavior negatively.

Let's assume that you want to eat fried chicken. There are two options: make yourself or use delivery system. For first option, you should go to wanted and buy some ingredients such as chicken. With other options, you only have to call restaurant. Imagine doing these steps without automobile. Delivery man should walk and takes an hour or more, fried chicken will takes cold. More fundamentally, how do you get chicken? I think automobile gives big great impact to our modern life.

Logistics is very important in our life and global. In this perpectation, automobile has improved a lot. Nowadays logistics happening in far distance that we cannot imagine without car, airplane, ship. That makes we can receive whatever we want within only few days, over the mountains, rivers, and seas.

Improving logistics is also good for technological improvement. we can transfer information and material efficiency. For example, when we make smartphone, we just order to deliver semiconductor, display, etc. and their specs. When we need security, automobile is helpful, too. Hand-carry have so many weakness to protect their cargo. but nowadays we can protect carefully with the automobile. U.S. president can survive at nuclear bomb within his own car.

Automobile gives us safe environment such as closed, private space when moving. In past, so many people are died by cold or hot weather, animal like tiger, etc. But we can survive nowadays at this situation by only following safety instructions.

Moving is huge part of logistics and our life. Walking and running are the most inefficient ways to transport. So automobile improves huge part of our modern life.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The world of media
 Nowadays the most of people use visual media to spend their time. Some people says visual media is just a blackhole that eats our valuable time. However, visual media has a very important role for our life.
 First of all, watching visual media is not a waste of time. We can learn many things from visual media. For example, we can learn Korea's financial history from Jaebulgipmaknaeadeul which is a Korean drama, and also different common sences fom Youtube. I knew that if I turn on the fan while I'm sleeping, I die, but I realized that is just a fake. For these reasons, we can educate many things through the visual medias.
 Next, visual media makes us experiment other's lives. Without an experience of love, we can see and hear the love... and apply them to our lives. Without an experience of the war, we can experiment the danger of the war, and we won't do the war again. We get many thoughts from visual media and then we can apply them to out lives.
 Finally, through the visual media, we can fulfill our lacked emotions. For instance, solos may watch romance, and fulfill their lacked loving mind... or by watching funny video, we can recharge our body, and get a power to live our lives. We can get a brain massage from visual media!
 To sum up, visual media is not just a waste of time, but textbook, fiction book, and best seller of our lives. This is just a change of the form. Even though the form is changed, the true thing inside of it is never changes. We should utilize visual media actively.

peerEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: Importance of Music
 Music gives to us happiness and peace. Some people believe music heal our soul. However, music play a essential role for our emotions.
 First of all, listening music is not a useless activity. We can learn many cultures through music. For instance, we can explore the history of Italy by opera, and discover unique instruments from Brazil. I thought that heavy metal cause harm, but realize it is use for expression. We can educate many rituals by music.
 Next, music makes us feel emotions we never experienced. Without having sadness, we can hear it in blues songs and understand the feeling. Without traveling the world, we can hear exotic sounds from different lands, and it inspire us. We get many sensations from music and we apply them to out lives.
 Finally, in music, we can fill our needed emotions. People who are alone listen love songs and satisfy their empty hearts... or by listening fast music, we recharge energy, and gain a power to continue. It is like a therapy for the brain!
 To conclude, music is not just a distraction, but a teacher, comforter and friend of our life. Even if form change, the rhythm inside always stays the same. We must admire music always.

Have you ever lived in a dormitory? Many people at KAIST have experienced living in dormitory. Depending on roommate, our life can be comfortable or uncomfortable. Then, what do you think are the qualities of a good roommate.
 I think there are three qualities of good roommate. 
 First, not be noisy. Do you know about biological time? Bio time is pattern of when we sleep, eat. It is important to keep rhythm. According to research, if bio time is broken, expect life decreases. Therefore, we have to be respect bio time of our roommate. But each people have various bio time. When you talk with your friends, somebody is sleeping. So we should be quiet to be respect bio time of our roommate.
 Second, be clear. When I was 17, in high school, I had dirty roommate. He didn't take showers, threw food waste on the floor. Our room became  messier and messier, and eventually we did't have enough space to do something and smell like garbage can. This was the worst experience in my life. After this experience, I realize cleanliness is very important. So I think when we live with someone, we should keep our room clean.
 Lastly, be respect privacy time. Even though we live with somebody, we want privacy time. If we can't be respect privacy time, we will be tired and maybe fight with roommate. Privacy time is one of the most important in life. It is can increase creativity, and be charge energy to work. So we should be respect privacy time.
 In conclusion, I think these three things are the most important qualities of roommate because these things are to be respect our roommate. If you are quiet, clear, and respect to privacy time, you will be good roommate.

studentEssay:
Can't we just work 4days per week?
Yes we can't. I firmly believe that we have to work 5 days per week. There are two main reasons about it : Economic depression and society problems. Let's go deeply about these. 
The first main reason is Economic depression. Economic system will be damaged in many ways if we change into 4-day work. For example, companies will lose their efficiency of producing, and many people will lose their job. And it will leaded to economic depression.
The second main reason is about laws and society problems. Since many laws are fitted to 5-day working, the change must involve a change of laws too. During the law-changing days, people may feel confused. And it can be leaded to some society problems such as sabotage.
For these reasons, we can't work only 4 days per week. Maybe 4-day working is great, but our society is not ready to accept such a big change. 
Thank you for reading.

peerEssay:
Should we eat more organic food? Yes we shouldn't. Organic food is often seen as a healthy choice. However, there are two main reasons why it's not the best option: High prices and limited availability. Let's go inspect these. 
Organic food often comes with a high price tag. Many families can't afford buy such expensive groceries regularly. Additionally, the production cost is high, and this price will passed to consumers.
Another reason is availability. Organic products are not easy to find in every store. People may have to travel far to get them, which is not always convenience. And this can leaded to unnecessary travel pollution.
For these reasons, we shouldn't eat only organic food. It's good idea, but it comes with problems that not everyone is ready to handle. Thank you for reading.

  Firstly, 2 days are very short and unbalanced. We work 5 days and rest 2 days, then it can't give perfect rest for us. If we aren't take a rest efficient, we can't work efficient, also. That is not good for all of us.
  Secondly, we need to time for self-training. We do not only work but also self-training. For example, we can spend time for learning about programming, singing or writing some books, etc. These times make your skills develop and raise your work efficiency.
  Lastly, we don't need to work harder than before. AI can do many simple works faster than people. So, we don't need to work long time. We have to concentrate our own work and have to think what should we do and what AI can't do. We train our mind and have creativity more than before.
  In conclusion, for three reasons, I think that we need 4-day work week. These days system is not efficient for work and we have to spend time for not only works also self-training. 4-day work gives times people to take some rest and develop some skills. I hope it will be changed to 4-day work week.

  The point of each reasons are same. "Decreasing work-times". It can cause some bad side effects. So, 5-days work week is better way than 4-days work week.

revised_essay:
Five-day work week had been the general rule until last 10 years. But now, new opinion about working days has emerged; 4-day work per week. Main background to appear this opinion is the balance of work and life, but it can causes some negative side effects. 
 First of all, if we started 4-day work week, the effective of work will be decreased. Think it easy. If working days are decreased, the amount of work which be given to each employees is increased. It can cause the increasing of working stress. Also, if we decline work-days, the time that employee focused hard to new work is declined, and it will be make more time to finish some work.
 Additionally, adjusting vacation times according to each company's situation is better than to take d-ay work week. The amount work of each companies required are different. Also, in one company, belong to the season or flow of society, the difficulty of work can change. For this reason, to adjust the length of vacation is better idea than to start 4-day work week.
  The point of each reasons are same. "Decreasing work-times". It can cause some bad side effects. So, 5-days work week is better way than 4-days work week.
peerEssay:
Eating balanced meals is very important to have good health. But recently, many people skip breakfast and lunch because busy schedules. This habit may look harmless at first, but have some negative impact. Firstly, if people not eat regularly, their energy levels is low. Consider this easily. If meals are missed, the energy for daily activity are reduced. It result in feeling tired and less focused. Moreover, without proper meals, body cannot get the essential nutrients. So, it becomes more time for body to repair itself and stay strong. 
 Additionally, having snack instead of meal can be harm. The ingredients in many snacks are full with sugar and fat, which not provide the nutrients body needs. In different situation, like during illness, sticking to good meal is more crucial than replace with snacks. For these reasons, having proper meal schedule is vital.
 At the end, in every situation, regular balanced meals are important. Without them, health will not good as it should be.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The way to make your life abundant, Studying abroad!

Today, I’m going to talk about studying abroad. Is studying abroad necessary for students? In my case, I think studying abroad makes our life better. So I want to study abroad after graduation of college. These are some reasons which support my opinion.

First, studying abroad leads to new experience which makes your life abundant. If you go to other country, there are lots of things (including buildings, culture) not familiar with you. These may help you to get a new idea. Furthermore, not be limited in your hometown can make you get new eyesight. For example, I traveled to New York City, one of the biggest cities in the world, when I was in high school. To compare the difference between Seoul and New York City, actually Seoul has developed too fast which makes the distribution of buildings a little complicated. In contrast, New York city has developed gradually which makes city organized. I also experienced a tip culture and at Smithsonian museum, I watched many sculpture of organisms that I had learned about during evolution and taxonomy class. So studying abroad helps you to get a new experience.

Second, you can have a relationship with new people. Relationship is important because when you get in trouble, you can receive a support and encouragement from your people. For instance, when you do a business, a relationship with employers, other companies are necessary to keep your business stable. So more various people you meet, more abundant your life.

To summarize, there are two benefits, new experience and relationship, of studying abroad. There should be a correlation between studying abroad and life quality, why don’t you go to abroad to get new friends and experience.

studentEssay:
During this fast-paced globalisation, visual media consists of some quick dopamine shots, also known as instant gratification, with platforms such as movies, TV, Netflix, YouTube, and more. These allow the public to watch what they desire with one click away. In some cases, individuals who have not established a sufficient personal principle, critical thinking, and self-control possibly digest these media like a double-edged sword. Hence, I believe it is likely that visual media affects individuals' behaviour negatively, which will be elaborated in the following paragraphs. 

To begin with, individuals need to apprehend a particular understanding of morality and own their personal principles. Many of these entertainments depict violence, non-PG13 elements, or taboo issues, which could contrast with their societal values. For instance, 'Euphoria', which is a well-known Netflix series surrounding a US high school theme. It consists of the teen's party life, the narcotics market dispersion and usage, LGBTQ+, and more things which might result in the fantasy of people who lack principle, thinking, "Wow, this is how life should be!". I acknowledge that does not mean it should be prohibited as an entertainment, but especially if underage children who have come across the show can easily be misguided in moral or principle. 

Consequently, in interpreting what is wrong and right from media information, critical thinking is needed. Namely, YouTube, in which people may distribute any content they wish to upload, despite the accuracy of information, sometimes spreads hoaxes or unconfirmed ideas, which could respond to mass hysteria that has not been factually proven.

Furthermore, with easy access towards these media, individuals may lose restraint sense of time and place, being too occupied with the more interesting, visually pleasing materials, procrastinate and be directed from the things that actually should be accomplished, but have been lowered in productivity. 

In conclusion, numerous negative impacts can be exposed to one's mind from taking certain ideas bluntly from the media. However, if a mind is grown and mature enough, it will be established just fine.

peerEssay:
As the world becomes increasing connected, social media has become a powerful tool for communication. Platforms like Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter keep us in touch with friends and family around the globe, with a just few clicks. However, not everyone has develop skills to use these responsibly, which can lead to problems. I suspect that social media may contribute negatively to personal relationships, a point that I will discuss more in detail soon. 

Firstly, people need to be capable of understanding how online interaction compares to real life. Often, these platforms present an idealised version of life, involving perfect photos and lifestyles that could conflict with their personal views. For example, Instagram influencers might portray their daily routines in way that many individuals try to mimic without consideration of their own situations, believing "This is the way I should live!". This does not suggest we need to ban these platforms as they provide entertainment and information, but younger audiences who see these posts might be easily influenced and misguided by idealised standards. 

Additionally, seeing through what is genuine or fake on social platforms requires critical thinking abilities. For instance, Twitter often becomes a place where misinformation spreads swiftly due to the ability of anyone to share any tweet they want, even if they are not true, leading to confusion among users.

Finally, with the chronic presence of social media every moment, some people might lose track of the time and neglect real world responsibilities, becoming entangled with endless scrolling, memes, and likes, which can reduce their overall effectiveness and focus on important tasks, thus lowering productivity. 

To sum up, various negative effects could impact an individual's perspectives if social platform messages are taken at face value. Nevertheless, well-grounded and mature mind could handle them appropriately.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The world of media
 Nowadays the most of people use visual media to spend their time. Some people says visual media is just a blackhole that eats our valuable time. However, visual media has a very important role for our life.
 First of all, watching visual media is not a waste of time. We can learn many things from visual media. For example, we can learn Korea's financial history from Jaebulgipmaknaeadeul which is a Korean drama, and also different common sences fom Youtube. I knew that if I turn on the fan while I'm sleeping, I die, but I realized that is just a fake. For these reasons, we can learn many things through the visual medias.
 Next, visual media makes us experience the other's lives. Without an experience of love, we can see and hear the love and apply them to our lives. Without an experience of the war, we can experiment the danger of the war, and we won't do the war again. We get many thoughts from visual media and then we can apply them to out lives.
 Finally, through the visual media, we can fulfill our lacked emotions. For instance, alone people may watch romance, and fulfill their lacked loving mind or by watching funny video, we can recharge our body, and get a power to live our lives. We can get a brain massage from visual media!
 To sum up, visual media is not just a waste of time, but textbook, fiction book, and best seller of our lives. This is just a change of the form. Even though the form is changed, the true thing inside of it is never changes. We should utilize visual media actively.

peerEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The importance of rest
 In the modern days, the most of people underestimate the value of rest. Some people think rest means sitting lazily and doing nothing. However, rest is needed part of our lives.
 First of all, rest helps to recharge the human energy. We can feel more energetic after a short nap. For example, by taking a walk in the park, which helps us relax, and also taking deep breaths from nature. I believed that if I rest too much, I become lazy, but then I learned that is not true. Therefore, rest is very beneficial to our bodies minds.
 Next, rest allows us to reflect on own life. Without proper rest, we keep running and miss many important life moments. Without a break, we reduce our ability to solve the problems, and we cannot handle stress effectively. We gain many insights from resting and can incorporate them into our future plans.
 Finally, rest brings us joy and happiness. For instance, tired people may listen to music, and fulfill their empty souls or by stopping work, we can release tension, and become refreshed for next tasks. We can get a mental recharge from resting!
 To conclude, rest is not merely being idle, but a refresh button, inspiration spark, and mood enhancer of our days. Even though we sometimes see it as waste, the true benefits within rest are invaluable. We should embrace rest in our lives.

studentEssay:
I heard that people watch Youtube for 40 hours per a month, roughly. It is huge. Visual media has many funny contents, so the time people spend on it may increases. However, it is not happy for me to hear that because I think that visual media influences people's behavior negatively. Why I think like that? Let me explain more.
First, I felt that visual media influences people's behavior negatively when I heard what my brother says like. When my brother was given his own phone, he spent more time watching Youtube. Then he said like Youtubers. His tone and words got rough, and he easily lost his anger during just normal dialog. Comparing the time when he said more softly, I found that the difference was the time he watched Youtube. In addition, given that teenagers are said not to be able to communicate well, visual media is likely to has to do with negative behavior.
Second, visual media seeks profit, so it easily uses extreme action. For example, in Korean manner, it is not polite to eat noodle generating big sound. However, comedians eat noodle generating big sound to interest people and highlight how deliciously they could eat. After that, people more eat noodle with big sound. I heard that people watch Youtube for 40 hours per a month, roughly. It is huge. Visual media has many funny contents, so the time people spend on it may increases. However, it is not happy for me to hear that because I think that visual media influences people's behavior negatively. Why I think like that? Let me explain more.
First, I felt that visual media influences people's behavior negatively when I heard the way my brother said. When my brother was given his own phone, he spent more time watching Youtube. Then he said like Youtubers. His tone and words got rough, and he easily lost his anger during just normal dialog. Comparing the time when he said more softly, I found that the difference was the length of time he watched Youtube. In addition, given that teenagers are said not to be able to communicate well, visual media is likely to has to do with negative behavior.
Second, since visual media seeks profit, it easily uses extreme action. For example, in Korean manner, it is considered not polite to eat noodle generating big sound. However, comedians ate noodle generating big sound to interest people and highlighted how deliciously they could eat. After that, people more ate noodle with big sound. So, I think visual media spread impolite manners.
Third, as we spend more time watching visual media, our brain more easily get tired. Then we cannot focus on our main work, easily make mistakes, more think negatively. It can influence the region of brain which controls behavior and other except visual sense, negatively. I watched negative behavior due to visual media, and I mentioned ones of that experiences in the previous paragraph. Visual media's influence is not so good, so we need to give effort to use visual media properly and not too much.

Many countries face the challenge of pollution today. It is growing rapidly. Air pollution is having big impacts on health, so the government's actions may affects people's lives. However, it is not enough to simply blame them because we think that pollution has many sources. How we think about it? Let us discuss more.
The first problem is that factories release harmful gases into the air. I thinks that these emissions are dangerous when I see the smoke factories releases. The sky becomes gray, and it feels unhealthy to breathe when close to factories. Compare to time before industrialization, I found that air quality was cleaner. In addition, given that cities are said to contribute heavily to pollution, industrial activity is likely to have to do with decreasing air quality.
Second, vehicles run on fuels that cause pollution, so people prefer them for convenience. For example, in many places, it is considered efficient to use cars even for short distances. However, more people prefer public transport, pollution isn't reduced fast.
Lastly, as we progress technologically, pollution more easily become a bigger issue. Then, controlling it is complex, easily causes debates, more needs solutions. It can affect global climate change which impacts many regions negatively. I observed pollution issues before, and I explained some of these problems earlier. Pollution's impact is not so small, so we need efforts to control it properly and quickly.

In my opinion, the visual medias can have both positive and negative influence on people's behavior, depending on the age of the user, the contents that are being watched, and how much time they spend to use it. For example, when children watch TV or Youtube, overtime they can become addicted to it and it can impact to their habits, such as being lazy. Regarding this, the parents have an important role to limit both screen time and the contents that are being watched by their children. 

However, visual medias can also be beneficial for people. For example, when people use it to watch the news or to study. In addition, there are many videos about school materials on Youtube that students can use to study. 

In conclusion, visual medias can influence people's habits both positively and negatively, depending on the screen time and the contents that are being watched.

peerEssay:
The importance of regular exercise is critical for maintaining a healthy lifestyle. There is various reasons why exercise is beneficial. Firstly, regular exercise helps to keep the heart healthy, and reduce the risk of many diseases like diabetes or hypertension. It is also improve mental health. Exercise releases endorphins in the brain, which contributes to improve mood and reducing anxiety.

Moreover, exercise can also help with maintaining a healthy weight. By burning calories through physical activities, such as jogging, cycling or swimming, one can prevent weight gain and keep fit. Age doesn't matter when it come to the effects of exercising.

However, it is necessary to be careful when starting a workout routine. Without proper knowledge, there might be a risk to injury. Additionally, a remaining hydrated and having necessary rest is essential to prevent overtraining. Overall, exercise have a significant impact on health, and it plays a crucial role in a person's well-being.

studentEssay:
Title: Imagine your life without the automobile. What would it be like?
In last June, I tripped Switzland just for travel. The airplane was so boring but it took me Switzland from South Korea in 13 hours. Thanks to it, I could travel for 14 days and spent just a day for moving countries.
In modern life, the automobile become one of most important things. We use cars, trams, trains, buses, ships, and airplanes. We often use it to get to work, trip the other cities or countries, and even for war or sports. Then what would be like if all automobiles suddenly disappeared?
At first, our work would become too inefficient. We cannot meet easily like before and contacting foreigners for business in offline become almost impossible. It is serious because we works with foreigners a lot of times nowadays. For example, conference from various country can be held 1 time or 2 times per a year because of old mobile like horses. This would causes the less improvement for science and math.
Second, the size of import and export would very smaller without the automobile. In modern life, we can eat beef from U.S. and coffee roasted with coffee bean in Africa. Without automobile, all we eat would be restricted and become more expensive. With import and export, countries could grow up by developing what they can make well and exchanging it.
Third, trip to other cities or countries would become impossible. If we don't have automobiles, we should spend at least 10 day to go to Busan from Daejeon. Furthermore, we can't even go China because of North Korea. Someone might think it is not necessary but for some cities, trip is most earning parts among any other industries.
Automobile have some serious problems. Earth pollution, used in war, and some like that. However, we cannot even live 'modern life' without the automobile. We should find solutions for automobile's problems, not arguing we have to prohibit automobiles.
The automobile obviously improved countries, cities and individuals so far.

peerEssay:
Title: The influence of technology on daily communication
In recent years, I talked many countries using advanced technology. The smartphone is crucial, but it let me communicate with people in different time zones. Technology is one of most significant developments. We utilize phones, computers, internet, email, and social media. We frequently use it to stay in touch with family, conduct business, or share information. But how would it be like if all technology suddenly cease to exist?
First, our personal lives would become more isolated. We cannot easily connect like before, and gaining new friends online become nearly unattainable. It is important because we keeps contact with friends internationally now. For example, conversation from several individual can only take place few times a year due to old fashion letters. It might hinder progress in building relationships.
Second, the availability of information would be drastic reduced without the technology. Nowadays, we access news globally and learn things occurring anywhere instantly. Without technology, our knowledge would limited and news delayed. People could not develop quickly and adapting to changes will face obstacles.
Third, reaching out to anyone or making emergency calls would become problematic. If we lack technology, alert others in emergencies would take hours instead of seconds. People might think it is unnecessary, but in some situations, timely responses are essential to saving lives.
Technology poses challenges, environment harm, misuse, and similar problems. However, we can't fully enjoy 'new era' without it. We need to resolve technology issues, not banish its progress.
Technology has evidently enhance personal and global connections so far.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The world of media
 Nowadays the most of people use visual media to spend their time. Some people says visual media is just a blackhole that eats our valuable time. However, visual media has a very important role to our life.
 First of all, watching visual media is not a waste of time. We can learn many things from visual media. For example, we can learn Korea's financial history from Jaebulgipmaknaeadeul which is a Korean drama, and also different common sences fom Youtube. I knew that if I turn on the fan while I'm sleeping, I die, but I realized that is just a fake. For these reasons, we can learn many things through the visual medias.
 Next, visual media makes us experience the other's lives. Without an experience of love, we can see and hear the love and apply them to our lives. Without an experience of the war, we can experiment the danger of the war, and we won't do the war again. We get many thoughts from visual media and then we can apply them to out lives.
 Finally, through the visual media, we can fulfill our lacked emotions. For instance, alone people may watch romance, and fulfill their lacked loving mind or by watching funny video, we can recharge our body, and get a power to live our lives. We can get a brain massage from visual media!
 To sum up, visual media is not just a waste of time, but textbook, fiction book, and best seller of our lives. This is just a change of the form. Even though the form is changed, the true thing inside of it never changes. We should utilize visual media actively.

For example, we can learn Korea's financial history from Jaebulgipmaknaeadeul which is a Korean drama, and also learn different common sences fom Youtube. I knew that if I turn on the fan while I'm sleeping, I die, but I realized that is just a fake. For these reasons, we can learn many things through the visual medias.
 Next, visual media makes us experience the other's lives. Without an experience of love, we can see and hear the love and apply them to our lives. Without an experience of the war, we can experiment the danger of the war, and we won't do the war again. We get many thoughts from visual media and then we can apply them to out lives.
 Finally, through the visual media, we can fulfill our lacked emotions. For instance, alone people may watch romance movie, and fulfill their lacked loving mind or by watching funny video, we can recharge our body, and get a power of living our lives. We can get a brain massage from visual media!
 To sum up, visual media is not just a waste of time, but textbook, fiction book, and best seller of our lives. This is just a change of the form. Even though the form is changed, the true thing inside of it never changes. We should utilize visual media actively.
peerEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: Importance of physical exercise
 Regular physical exercise is crucial for maintaining good health. Some doctors suggests that it is the most effective way to prevent illnesses. However, physical exercise can offer many other benefits to our well-being.
 First, doing physical exercise is not a waste of energy. We can improve several aspects of our health from different kinds of exercises. For example, jogging can enhance heart health and swimming can strengthen muscles. I used to think that any exercise after evening will hurt sleep, but I discovered that it is not true. For these reasons, we can gain many benefits through the physical exercise.
 Next, physical activity helps us connect with others. Without the experience of teamwork in sports, we can understand and feel cooperation by playing games. Without the experience of a competition, we can understand the thrill of winning, and will want to strive for success. We acquire new perspectives from physical activities and we can apply them in everyday life.
 Finally, through physical exercise, we can manage our emotions. For example, lonely people can join group activities, filling their lack of companionship, or by engaging in yoga, we can relax our mind and find peace. We get a good mental boost from physical exercise!
 To end, physical exercise is not just efforts and sweat, but a way to enrich our lives. This is simply a form of self-care. Despite any form, the truth inside it remains constant. We should embrace regular physical activity actively and often.

studentEssay:
Have you heard about cases where talented students go abroad to study?
Perhaps to Harvard, MIT, Oxford, and other prestigious universities. For many Korean students, such schools are seen as symbols of academic excellence.

However, I believe it is not necessary for students to study abroad.

First, Korea already has many excellent universities such as SNU, KAIST, and Yonsei. Many professors here have studied overseas, so they can provide students with diverse perspectives. Therefore, those who want to learn from outstanding professors can do so without leaving Korea.

Second, we are living in the 21st century, a time when students can meet and interact with others online. The main benefit of studying abroad is the opportunity to meet people from different backgrounds and share ideas, but today’s technology already makes this possible.

In conclusion, studying abroad is not essential for students. Although it has benefits, studying in our own country is also a valuable option. The development of domestic universities and advanced technology allows students to gain knowledge beyond national boundaries.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The Fact : Benefits of Automobile

These days automobiles are the most important transportation, and most of modern people use it everyday. People do not just walk or ride bicycle for travel. They usually use cars, trains or planes. Even if it is a short distance, people uses electric scooter. As people use it casually, lots of problems are occurring these days. Car crash, Parking lots, and air pollution are one of the most serious problems of these days. However, in my opinion, automobile give us benefits a lot more than problems. Therefore research and development of automobiles should be continued.

It seems like automobile just hurts people. It is because of the news that shows about car crash, air pollution or the other automobile accidents. Even though it causes serious problem directly, it saves lots of people indirectly. Ambulances transport patients to the hospitals so that many people could save their lives. 119 (or 911) rushes to the place where accidents occured which make lots of people’s life goes on. Additionally, automobile produce fast transport and delivery, so it made development much faster, and the development made people live much longer and healthier.

Next, we should keep developing our technologies even if there are some serious problems. According to second paragraph, automobile has not only problems, but also benefits about people’s lives. It is true that there are many problems with automobile. However, if we give up developing automobile, we could not get more advanced technologies. Although we have some sacrifices, we should go ahead so that we could save more lives in the future. It is important to look far away ahead.

As automobile came out and it gave us comfort which we couldn’t feel before, we can not go back. Therefore, we should keep using automobile so that it can get better and better. It is a better way for the future.

ESSAY TITLE: The Value of Education

Education is an very important part of modern society, and many people sees it as a key to success. People do not just learn at home or through experience. majority usually attend schools, universities, or online courses. Even if it is a short course, individuals use online platforms. As education evolves, a lots of challenges occur today. Student debt, inequality, and outdated syllabus are some of the issues faced now. However, I believe education provides us more advantages than challenges. Hence, committing resources to the education system is crucial.

It may seem like education only create pressure on students. It is because of stories about student stress, high debt, and exam failures. Even though it cause stress directly, it contributes more benefits indirectly. Schools prepare students for successful careers so many could achieve their dreams. Universities drive innovation, making people's lives progressing. Additionally, education promote critical thinking and problem-solving, which leads to societal improvement.

Next, investing in our educational institutions should continue despite any serious problems. According to previous paragraph, education not only includes challenges but also have numerous benefits to people. It is true that issues exist within the education system. However, if we stop investing in it, we won't see advancement in many fields. Although some sacrifices is needed, continuing forward is essential so we can have better societies tomorrow. It is vital to look far forward.

Without education’s growth and providing knowledge we never had, returning to the past is not option. Thus, we must keep embracing education so that it could improve continually. It is way forward for the future.

What do you ride for a trip? Of course you have to fly by airplane to go to other country or Jeju-do, but you probably have to use car, autobike, or some kind of automobile. It makes you more faster than your own legs or non-moter bike. Just imagine you are in 300 years ago. You should walk for a month to go Seoul from Busan. But now? You can go to Seoul from Busan in few hours by car.

This is not the only benefit of automobile. automobile have improved many area. The biggest thing automobile did is supply transportation. In the past, people can’t deliver supply to far place. Because it takes so many times, money, and if they deliver food, it can be rotten. So people can’t make a large market. Instead, they just share and sell their stuff to village or in family. But when automobile start to use, it changed game. People able to transport their supply further, so market get bigger. The flow of money became faster, civilization grow bigger.

The other thing automobile improved did is human’s comfort.

We can move faster by using automobile. It makes people can travel various place, go to their work faster. In the past, people usually lived in village, even for a lifetime. But now we live in big city (not every people) and we can go to company that distance from our home is 50km!

It is true that automobile makes accident and global warming, but this problem can be solved by technology, and automobile brings so many benefit for our life. So, I agree with people who think the automobile has improved modern life.
