peerEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The Importance of Learning Languages

Today, learning languages are very important for modern people. Everyone should learn at least one language aside from their mother tongue. People use language not just for communication or writing letters. They require it for reading books, traveling abroad, or doing business internationally. Although it is difficult, people learns new language quickly these days. As more people engage in language studies, numerous benefits arise. Cultural exchange, new friendships, and better job opportunities is among the most exciting prospects. However, I believe learning languages has more advantages than it seems. Therefore pursuing language education should be encouraged further.

It appears like language learning takes a lot of effort. This is because learning a new language can be challenging and require a lot of time. Even though it takes much dedication, it make communication easier globally. Bilinguals and polyglots communicate effectively across different countries, proving beneficial for diplomacy and global trade. Speaking multiple languages promotes understanding across cultures and enhances personal growth. Additionally, multi-language capabilities open doors to education from institutions worldwide, making knowledge accessible and life richer.

Next, we should continue to encourage language studies, even if it requires effort and time investment. As mentioned in the second paragraph, learning languages has not only challenges but also offers numerous personal benefits. It is real that mastering a new language may take years. However, if we give up we cannot enjoy these benefits. Although there are sacrifices needed, we should push forward to gain greater understanding of the world. Preparing our future generations with language skills is crucial for a brighter future.

Given how learning languages has enriched our lives, it is clear that stopping is not an option. Subsequently, we should persist in language study so it becomes increasingly beneficial. This drive towards multilingualism is our best plan for a diverse and inclusive future.

What do you ride for a trip? Of course you have to fly by airplane to go to another country or Jeju-do, but you probably have to use car, autobike, or some kind of automobile. It makes you faster than your own legs or non-motor bike. Just imagine you are in 300 years ago. You should walk for a month to go from Busan to Seoul. But now? You can go to Seoul from Busan in few hours by car.

This is not the only benefit of automobiles. Automobiles have improved many areas. The biggest thing automobile did is supply transportation. In the past, people couldn't deliver supplies to far places. Because it took too much time, money, and if they deliver food, it could be rotten. So people couldn't make a large market. Instead, they just share and sell their stuff to village or in family. But when automobile started to be used, it changed game. People were able to transport their supply further, so market got bigger. The flow of money became faster, civilization grew bigger.

The other thing automobile improved did is human’s comfort.

We can move faster by using automobile. It makes people can travel various place, go to their work faster. In the past, people usually lived in village, even for a lifetime. But now we live in big city (not every people) and we can go to company that distance from our home is 50km!

It is true that automobile makes accident and global warming, but this problem can be solved by technology, and automobile brings so many benefit for our life. So, I agree with people who think the automobile has improved modern life.

studentEssay:
ESSAY TITLE: The Fact : Benefits of Automobile

These days automobiles are the most important transportation, and most of modern people use it everyday. People do not just walk or ride bicycle for travel. They usually use cars, trains or planes. Even if it is a short distance, people uses electric scooter. As people use it casually, lots of problems are occurring these days. Car crash, Parking lots, and air pollution are one of the most serious problems of these days. However, in my opinion, automobile give us benefits a lot more than problems. Therefore research and development of automobiles should be continued.

It seems like automobile just hurts people. It is because of the news that shows about car crash, air pollution or the other automobile accidents. Even though it causes serious problem directly, it saves lots of people indirectly. Ambulances transport patients to the hospitals so that many people could save their lives. 119 (or 911) rushes to the place where accidents occured which make lots of people’s life goes on. Additionally, automobile produce fast transport and delivery, so it made development much faster, and the development made people live much longer and healthier.

Next, we should keep developing our technologies even if there are some serious problems. According to second paragraph, automobile has not only problems, but also benefits about people’s lives. It is true that there are many problems with automobile. However, if we give up developing automobile, we could not get more advanced technologies. Although we have some sacrifices, we should go ahead so that we could save more lives in the future. It is important to look far away ahead.

As automobile came out and it gave us comfort which we couldn’t feel before, we can not go back. Therefore, we should keep using automobile so that it can get better and better. It is a better way for the future.

ESSAY TITLE: The Fact : Importance of Healthy Eating

Nowadays healthy eating is one of the most important lifestyle choices, and most of people tries to eat nutritious food daily. People do not just eat fast food or snacks all the time. They usually choose fresh fruits, vegetables or whole grains. Even if it is a small meal, people prefers organic ingredients. As people pay attention, lots of changes are happening these days. Health issues, weight management, and energy levels are one of the most common issues of these days. However, in my opinion, healthy eating provides benefits far more than these issues. Therefore, study and promotion of healthy eating should be encouraged.

It seems like healthy eating just take too much effort. It is because of advertisements and social media which talk about fad diets or unrealistic body images. Even though healthy eating requires planning, it eventually results in more energy and better health. Nutritionists provide guidance on balanced diets so that many people maintain their health. Chefs innovate with healthy recipes which lets lots of people’s meals becomes nutritious and tasty. Additionally, healthy eating promotes self-care and well-being, so it leads to positive lifestyle changes that make people's life longer and fuller.

Moreover, we should continue encouraging healthy habits even if there are obstacles. According to second paragraph, healthy eating has not only challenges, but also enhancement on people’s lives. It is evident that there are hurdles in maintaining a healthy diet. However, if we stop promoting healthy eating, future generations might not enjoy a healthy life. Although we face some difficulties, we need to proceed so that we can improve quality of life for everyone. It is important to think about the long term benefits.

As healthy eating has been adopted and it brings advantages which we couldn’t experience before, we can not give it up. Therefore, we should keep eating healthily so that it enhances continuously. It is a better path for the future.

studentEssay:
In many countries, laborers, workers, and many people who literally "work" are expecting two days every week, which are Saturday and Sunday. The reason is simple. As everyone knows, those days are the only days in the week to be free from work and rest and chill. But some people think that two days of rest isn't enough. Some of them argue we should have a 4-day work week, not a 5-day work week as usual. This sounds cool to many workers, so for the happiness of many people, this argument looks persuasive and positive. However, changing the policy dramatically "for" the people conveys side effects with a high possibility. What kinds of side effects will this argument have?
To say an extremely economic system could collapse. The world is based on a 5-day work week now. Through the efforts of many researchers and historians, people believed that two free workdays were enough, and countries adopted this policy. However, let's suppose that one country changes it to a 4-day work week, so every company should give workers 3 free days. The first thing that will happen is that the GDP of the country will decrease. This will happen naturally because the time for working has been decreased. Then, how about the boss make it harder to prevent this situation? Well, I believe this could be more stressful for workers than a 5-day work week.

Technology in our modern society has become indispensable. Devices like smartphones and laptops keep us connected and helps us be productive. But is all of this technology really necessary? Some argue that we should limit technology use to regain more personal time and focus on family. This notion could sound ideal to many people, since spending all day on devices may lead to less time with loved ones. On contrary, changing the way we use technology abruptly can have negative consequences. What kind of problems might this cause?

Yet, imagine if we started restricting technology usage significantly, how businesses communication will suffer. The first problem is that engaging with clients and partners will become more difficult. Without real-time communication tools, productivity could decrease. If companies need to switch methods to maintain the existing standards, it might become more costly and cumbersome than simply allowing current technology use.

Some people say that "5-day work week is too ling and 2-day weekend is too short". So, they argue that we need to change 5-day work week to 4-day work week. This opinion has lots of advantage and most people also want 4-day work week. But, I think this opinion has more disadvantage. So I disagree there should be 4-day work week.

First reason that I disagree is if there is 4-day work week, we need more work on week. When 5-day work week changes 4-day work week, if we work same amount, result amount will decrease. So, we work more harder to fill decreased amount and this will lead to harder work in work week.

Second reason is we already have much time to spend our hobby time. Some people who agree 4-day work week argue that if we change work week, we spend enough time to enjoy hobby. Moreover, we also have free time on work week when we finish the work.

For this reason, I think that we don’t have to change 5-day work week to 4-day work week. 5-day work week also has many free time and didn’t need harder work.

peerEssay:
Many people argue that "School vacations are too short and students need more time off." They believe students should have longer vacation times. This idea seems to offer benefits and many students want it. However, I believe there are more drawbacks. So I disagree with extending the vacation period.

First reason why I disagree is extended vacations can lead to skill decline. When students have more time off, learning gaps increase. This could result in decreased academic performance, and students will work more harder when they return.

Second reason is students already have enough breaks. Some people who want longer vacations think students will have more time for hobbies and relaxation. But I believe students have sufficient vacation. Because during breaks, they can travel, play sports, and more. Moreover, students can relax on weekends even during the school year.

For these reasons, I think we should not extend school vacations. Current system has adequate breaks and doesn't require any change.

Why I Agree 4-day work week.

  These days, many people say change the number of working days 5 to 4. I really agree about this opinion.
  First, many people need more rest time. People work so hard or late, so people feel that rest time is not enough. Also, in Sunday, next day is working day. Thus, people can't rest freely, and, in these reason, we feel the weekend is too short.
  Second, 4 days are enough to work. People who don't agree 4-day work week say if we work 4 day, we don't have enough time to work. But I think differently. Many company, let working to employee 8 hours per day. So, if we work 10 hours per day, there is no different thing between 4-day work and 5-day work. Also, we rest 3 days, we didn't feel so long working time.
  Lastely, people have more free time, so people can do more various experiments. Now, people just have 2-day for free. But it is too short to move and play. So, if do 4-day work week, people can move far and do more many thing. In conclusion, people will be more happy.
  Like these, 4-day work week has more positive things than 5-day work week. So I strongly agree about that.

peerEssay:
The Benefits of Reading Books.

  In recent times, fewer people seem read books. I strongly believe this is a mistake. First, reading books help people learn new things. We can understand more about world or acquire skills reading books. Also, the information in book is often deeply researched. In result, we get a more complete view of topics. 
  Second, reading is a great way to relax. People often stress from work or school. Because of that, reading provide a peaceful escape. Moreover, it let us imagine different scenarios and worlds, which can be very refreshing.
  Thirdly, books can improve language skills. When we read books, we see how words are used in different ways. So, this can increase our vocabulary and improve our grammar. In addition, it help us express ideas more clearly.
  For last benefit, reading encourage creativity. People who read can think more widely and come up with new idea. If more people read books, society will become more innovative.
  As you see, reading books has more benefits than not reading. Thus, I encourage everyone to read more books.

studentEssay:
Today, people have different needs, so there are many types of work. In Korea, most companies follow a 5-day work week, but many people want a 4-day work week. I think there are many benefits to a 4-day work week.

First, work-life balance has become much more important than in the past. Money is also important, but spending time with family, resting, and having time for personal development are even more valuable these days. Having only two days of personal time per week is not enough.

Second, efficiency is more important than spending long hours at work. I think concentrating for a short time and achieving the best results is the most effective way to work. In Europe, some companies have already adopted a 4-day work week because they believe efficiency is the most important factor.

Third, companies can hire more employees. With a 4-day work week, each person may earn slightly less, allowing companies to employ more people. More employees bring diverse ideas, which can help the company develop and innovate.

In conclusion, considering people’s needs and company development, a 4-day work week is a better choice.

Nowadays, [the technology are] everywhere, it [affect] our lives in many ways.. Especially, smartphones have changed the way people communicate. They bring both advantages and disadvantages. 

Firstly, using smartphones allows us to stay in touch with others very easily. Wherever you are, you can quickly send message or call. This is much convenient than traditional ways. In addition, internet access through smartphones gives us information immediately, at any time. However, on the other hand, smartphones might cause us to spend less time with family. We often see family members sitting together, but they all are looking at their own phones.

Secondly, smartphones can improve education. With a smartphone, students can learn through online courses and access [a vast number of resources].... This is a great benefit for students, 

Also, excessive smartphone use can harm our health. Looking on a small screen for long hours can cause eye strain and headaches. Moreover, improper posture while using the phone may lead to neck and back pain. 

In conclusion, while smartphones provide many convenient features and aid in education, we should be mindful of its negative effects.

studentEssay:
In contemporary societies, we are exposed to many visual media like movies, TV, Netflix, and YouTube. Nowadays, most people can access to these visual media easily, so they become part of our life. And they give some new information, dopamine by watching them. But is this perfect for life?

Some dopamine may be needed for us, of course. But most visual media give more dopamine than enough amount to us. Visual media are very fateful interesting, so we watch more and more. Imagine the situation that the person watching YouTube shorts, and it’s time to sleep. This person may think “I will sleep after this video end”. But dopamine from video makes this person to see other video naturally. Although person turn off the phone, He (or she) think about YouTube video, so He (or she) cannot sleep early. Also, too many dopamines decrease our concentration. When you study after watch the visual media, you may think about what you see, so you cannot focus on study only, this may reduce your work ability. Supporting this opinion, the person who stop watching visual media and cut all dopamine, much more fast his work.

And getting information by visual media can be dangerous. Of course, there are much useful information in visual media. But you should remember there are much wrong information. Even, added movie animation, with wrong information, people are more easily believe that wrong information.

For this reason, we should reduce our time that watching visual media and increase our life quality.

And gaining knowledge by transport can be risky. Of course, there are much good experiences in travel. But you should remember there are much risky situations. Even, with extra speed, with risky situations, people are more easily engage in dangerous activities.

studentEssay:
Let's think about if all automobiles disappear suddenly in our life. What happens to us? After few hours, we may have to walk or ride a bicycle to go home. In this case, it's not serious problem. But after few days, we may not get any fresh foods and new things, the problem will become serious and make us harder to survive. You can realize that automobiles are very important to our lives with this example. So I want to say is that automobile is totally good for human's life.

We can't survive without automobile, but it also has some bad aspect. Most of recent automobiles still use engines which burn the fuel and make some greenhouse gases. So for the recent few centuries, uses of automobile heat the Earth and cause many serious nature issues. But it can be solved with development of electric vehicles. In addition to this, I want to emphasize that the use of automobile is not major causes of greenhouse effect anymore.

After the industrial revolution at 18th century, human has been able to manufacture almost everything with great amount. This decreases the price of each thing, so individual can buy car, foods and house. With the technique of manufacturing, we can make, for example, 1000000 water bottles in factory. But to distribute these manufactured bottles to individuals, we need transporting element. Since the automobile is the major part of transportation, without this, the human civilization can not maintain itself.

Imagine what if we wake up one day and all music disappear. How would our life change? Without music, the world may seem silent and boring. Music is important, but it also comes with some negative aspect. Some people play music very loudly, which disturb others. I emphasize that the conflicts caused by music is not very serious anymore.

With technology, we can produce many different songs in a short time. But to share this music with larger audience, we need distribution platforms. Since internet is major part of music sharing, without it, music industry cannot thrive.

studentEssay:
Let's think about if all automobiles disappear suddenly in our life. What happens to us? After few hours, we may have to walk or ride a bicycle to go home. In this case, it's not serious problem. But after few days, we may not get any fresh foods and new things, the problem will become serious and make us harder to survive. You can realize that automobiles are very important to our lives with this example. So I want to say is that automobile is totally good for human's life.

We can't survive without automobile, but it also has some bad aspect. Most of recent automobiles still use engines which burn the fuel and make some greenhouse gases. So for the recent few centuries, uses of automobile heat the Earth and cause many serious nature issues. But it can be solved with development of electric vehicles. In addition to this, I want to emphasize that the use of automobile is not major causes of greenhouse effect anymore.

After the industrial revolution at 18th century, human has been able to manufacture almost everything with great amount. This decreases the price of each thing, so individual can buy car, foods and house. With the technique of manufacturing, we can make, for example, 1000000 water bottles in factory. But to distribute these manufactured bottles to individuals, we need transporting element. Since the automobile is the major part of transportation, without this, the human civilization can not maintain itself.

Imagine if the internet suddenly disappears from our daily life. What will happen to us? After few hours, you may notice you cannot check emails or social media. In this case, it is not an urgent problem. But after few days, you may struggle to access important information and communication may become harder. This example shows internet is very essential for our daily life. So I want to emphasize internet is totally beneficial for human's interaction.

Life is difficult without internet, but it has some harmful aspect. Most of recently internet servers require a lot of energy which make pollution and increase carbon footprint. So for the last few years, usage of internet consume more resources and cause environmental problems. However, it is solved by development of renewable energy sources. In addition to this, I would like to say that the usage of internet is not significant cause of pollution anymore.

After the technology boom in 20th century, people have developed faster access to knowledge. This lowers the barrier to education, so individuals can gain skills, jobs, and entertain. With the internet tool, we can send, for example, thousands of messages every second. But to make this vast network function, we need powerful servers. Since the internet is the key part of modern communication, without it, our society cannot sustain its current pace.

People have hard times because people have to work a lot during their week. Someone thinks it is not truely effective. I think a 4-day work week is a great idea.

First of all, people need more time to refresh and make their own life function better. A 5-day work week is too short to have some break and solve personal problems. If there are some 4-day work week, it can help people to live more comfortablly and relaxed.

Second, 4-day work week makes employees work time effectively. In many case, 5-day work week is useless. People can do their week work in 4 days if there is no waste of time. In other word, maintaining 5-day work without special reasons is a large waste of time and money.

Lastly, 4-day work week can make employees feel more energized. People might love 4-day work week because extra holiday is very attractive. Many people do their best in their work because of these extra holiday.

In conclusion, 4-day work week can give people not only time to refresh but also effective working time. If there is 4-day work week, people feel cheerful and do their work well.

studentEssay:
Title : We can't live without automobile.

There are a lot of accident caused by automobile. About 10 years ago, there was a huge ship accident in Korea. Society was shocked and important national events were cancelled. Many people remember it for about 10 years. Last year, there was a airplane accident and many people died. Like these examples, automobile can cause serious problems. However I think they are necessary to our life. I will tell you why I think so.
 First, we can easily go far place with mobility. Everyday I take OLEV Bus to go classroom in W1 building. If I go there without any rides, I have to walk about 20 minutes. With automobile, we can go further and faster.
 Second, automobile can save people. If there's heart attack person, 119 car will come within safe time. If someone hurt in deep mountain, helicopter will go there and escape him or her. We can go another region to meet great doctor. We can get medicine from other country. All these can be because of automobile.
 Finally, accident done by transportation isn't its fault. We aware of fire. However no one think fire is the one to be exited from our life. Automobile is same as fire. It is dangerous but it is necessary. Accident happens due to not car but driver.
 Therefore, automobile makes us go anywhere easily, saves our lives, and accident isn't done by automobile. For these reasons, automobile has improved our life. If we use it wisely, we can reduce serious problem. We can't live without automobile.

peerEssay:
Title : The importance of water conservation.

Water is one of the most important resource in our daily life. Imagine if we wake up tomorrow, and there was no water anywhere. Everyone understand that water is essential to live, but many people forgets about this fact and waste water unnecessarily. In a different situation, there was an earthquake that cause people to worry about water supply. Many people stored the water ahead of time and it became scarce for others. However, I think we must use water wisely for several important reasons.
 First, water conservation help us save money. If people pays attention to their water usage, their water bills can be reduced. People does not think about how much money they lose by leaving a tap running. Saving money is important for everyone.
 Second, water conservation helps to protect our environment. By reducing our usage, we decrease the demand for water resources; this is beneficial for nature. When we need less water, water systems are less stressed and keeps the balance of nature. For example, fewer water usage means less energy needed to pump water to homes.
 Finally, the future of our planet depends on good use of water. Freshwater reserves are limited and they can gone soon if we don't act now. Just like a fire can be put out without using an extinguisher. We must take action before it is too late and save water for future generations. Water is crucial for daily life.
 For these reasons, water conservation helps save money, protects the environment, and is vital for the future. We should not ignore this and use water wisely.

I heard that people watch Youtube for 40 hours per a month, roughly. It is huge. Visual media has many funny contents, so the time people spend on it may increases. However, it is not happy for me to hear that because I think that visual media influences people's behavior negatively. Why I think like that? Let me explain more.
First, I felt that visual media influences people's behavior negatively when I heard the way my brother said. When my brother was given his own phone, he spent more time watching Youtube. peerEssay: Eating healthy foods can be important for good health. It is significant. Healthy foods has many vitamins, so the chance of getting ill may decreases. First, I felt that healthy foods are not always tasty when I tasted the salad my friend made. When my friend started cooking, he spent more time watching cooking shows. Then he cooked like chefs on television. His meals looked nice, but it didn't taste good, and I easily got bored with eating them. Comparing the times when he cooked simply, I found that the difference was the length of time he watched cooking shows. In addition, given that some people are said not to prefer vegetables, healthy foods is often has to do with tasteless meals. Second, since healthy food seeks to promote health, it easily dismisses flavorful ingredients. For example, in my culture, it is considered not polite to eat food that makes you grimace. However, health enthusiasts ate food that made them grimace to boast their discipline and highlighted how strong they were. After that, people more ate foods with less flavor. So, I think tasteless healthy foods spread negative views. Third, as we spend more time eating healthy foods, our taste more easily get bored. Then we cannot enjoy our meals, easily make flavorless dishes, more think negatively about food. It can influence the region of taste which controls our enjoyment and other flavors, negatively. studentEssay:
Today, there are lots of visual medias in this world. They are useful in giving information or enjoying our life. But, I think visual media do influence people behavior negatively.
 First, visual media make people follow their bad topics. Because they can be way to earn money, people who make visual media make them too much violent, catch people's eyes. So these traits lead particularly children to do something negative.
 Second, short form, one of the most interesting forms in visual media can make concentration of people low. We can easily touch short forms and can rapidly scroll the screen to watch more videos. Then, this moving can let our brain not concentrate other things.
 Last, visual media can have people believe non-fact incidents. Since the AI industry evolves, providing images or videos that we want though they are so fiction becomes easy. However, people believe easily what they see, so media can make people trust that media is real. 
 For these reasons, visual media can take negative efforts to people, I hope they provide a good affect to the world.

peerEssay:
Food plays crucial role in our life. It provide us with energy and important nutrients. But, I think food have negative effects on our health.
 First, fast foods are very popular among people. Because they save time, people often rely on fast foods. So these types of foods lead particularly young people to obesity.
 Second, high calorie snacks, one of the common food items, can affect health in bad way. We can easily buy and eat them without thinking. Then, this habit can let our health not be good.
 Last, processed food can make people get wrong health information. Since the food industry evolves, providing food that looks healthy is easy. However, people believe easily what packaging says, so food can trick people to think it is healthy.
 For these reasons, food can impact us negatively, I hope they bring positive impact on the society.

studentEssay:
Let's think about if all automobiles disappear suddenly in our life. What happens to us? After few hours, we may have to walk or ride a bicycle to go home. In this case, it's not serious problem. But after few days, we may not get any fresh foods and new things, the problem will become serious and make us harder to survive. You can realize that automobiles are very important to our lives with this example. So I want to say is that automobile is totally good for human's life.

We can't survive without automobile, but it also has some bad aspect. Most of recent automobiles still use engines which burn the fuel and make some greenhouse gases. So for the recent few centuries, uses of automobile heat the Earth and cause many serious nature issues. But it can be solved with development of electric vehicles. In addition to this, I want to emphasize that the use of automobile is not major causes of greenhouse effect anymore.

After the industrial revolution at 18th century, human has been able to manufacture almost everything with great amount. This decreases the price of each thing, so individual can buy car, foods and house. With the technique of manufacturing, we can make, for example, 1000000 water bottles in factory. But to distribute these manufactured bottles to individuals, we need transporting element. Since the automobile is the major part of transportation, without this, the human civilization can not maintain itself.

peerEssay:
Imagine if all computers vanish in our world. What happens next? After time, we might have to use papers to write or check books for information. In this moment, it is not big trouble. But after several weeks, access to digital content and communication will become impossible, and this problem will make life more difficult. This shows us clearly that computers are very essential to our modern life. So what I want to share is that computers play very good role in our daily life.

We can't imagine life without computer, but it also comes with some bad sides. Many current computers consume electricity which contributes to environmental damage. So in recent decades, the widespread use of computers has increased power demands and environmental problems. But these challenges can be tackled with renewable energy sources. Moreover, I want to underline that computers are not main reason of energy crisis now.

Since the digital age began, people have the ability to process huge amounts of information rapidly. This advancement lowered the cost of information, so anyone can access media, online courses and virtual goods. With technological advancement, we can produce, for example, millions of digital documents instantly. But to manage and spread these digital contents, we need a robust internet infrastructure. Since the computer is central to this network, without it, our current civilization would face severe difficulty.

studentEssay:
I had a question sometimes why we felt holidays was shorter than weekdays. It is because holidays are really shorter than weekdays. In a week, we have 5 days for a work and 2 days for a rest. Then, I think that there should be a 4-day work week. There are three reasons.
  First, 2 days are very short and unbalanced. We work 5 days and rest 2 days, then it can't give perfect rest for us. If we aren't take a rest efficiently, we can't work well, also. That is not good for all of us.
  Second, we need to time for self-training. We do not only work. For example, we can spend time for learning about programming, singing or writing some books, etc. These times make your skills develop and raise your work efficiency.
  Last, we don't need to work harder than before. AI can do many simple works faster than people. So, we don't need to work long time. We have to concentrate our own work and have to think what should we do and what AI can't do. We train our mind and have creativity more than before.
  In conclusion, for these three reasons, I think that we need 4-day work week. These days system is not efficient for work and we have to spend time for not only works also self-training. 4-day work gives times people to take some rest and develop some skills. I hope it will be changed to 4-day work week.

peerEssay: Many people wonder why desserts taste so good. It is because they are sweet, and we like sweets. For this reasons, I think everyone should enjoy desserts. There are multiple arguments. First, if we eat dessert, it makes us happy and satisfied. Desserts give us a good feeling after meals, and if we don't get this feeling, we might not complete enjoy our meal. Happiness can be important for our life. Second, desserts provide energy for our body. Foods like chocolate or ice creams have sugars, then these sugars give us quick energy to do our tasks better. Energy supply is very essential for everyday activity. Last, having desserts at end may be good for social events. People often talk and socialize when eating cakes or sweets together. Second, 4-day work week makes employees work time effectively. In many case, 5-day work week is useless. People can do their week work in 4 days if there is no waste of time. In other words, maintaining 5-day work without special reasons is a large waste of time and money.

In conclusion, 4-day work week can give people not only time to refresh but also effective working time. If there is 4-day work week, people feel cheerful and do their work well.

Imagine the situation that the person watching YouTube shorts, and it’s time to sleep. This person may think “I will sleep after this video end”. Also, too many dopamines decrease our concentration. When you study after watch the visual media, you may think about what you see, so you cannot focus on study only, this may reduce your work ability. The reading passage presents three potential solutions to prevent the extinction of the Torreya tree. However, the professor in the lecture disagrees with all of them and provides reasons why they are unlikely to be effective.
First, the reading suggests replanting the Torreya tree in its original habitat in Florida, where a unique microclimate once supported its growth. The professor, however, points out that due to climate change, this microclimate no longer exists, making the reintroduction of the tree to this area ineffective.
Second, the reading proposes relocating the Torreya tree to a colder region in the north, assuming that it may thrive in such a climate. The professor counters this by citing the example of the black locust tree, which, after being moved to a new area, grew excessively and caused damage to the local ecosystem.
Finally, the reading recommends cultivating the Torreya tree in research centers, enabling scientists to protect and study it. Nevertheless, the professor argues that trees grown in controlled environments tend to lose their natural resistance to diseases. Furthermore, replicating the extensive and diverse conditions required for the tree’s survival in the wild is highly challenging.

studentEssay:
In recent days, there rises an hot issue about whether to reduce working days, from five to four days a week. Under this new system, employees would work from Monday to Thursday or from Tuesday to Friday; otherwise, you may be able to choose which day to take a rest between weekdays. It has been a big trend spread from big tech and venture corporations in some regions of United States, in the direction of cutting working hours and helping utilization of each workers. The main reason for the uprising attention in Korea is the announcement of current(21st) Korean president, Lee Jae-Myeong, for introducing his promises for the president election held in this year.

He said that during his period, he would give a renewal of work time into 4-day work week ultimately, and would get started the shift into 4.5-day work week — Mon. to Thurs. are just the same, and finish a work week at noon, on Friday — until the next year. His keypoint was that there would be no deduction of salary, so he has been offended and criticized from many business runners and experts in economics.

But however, I think it is not the most important thing about these arguments to simply choose between 4-day and 5-day. In my opinion, work week needs to be adjusted with considering each company's condition, and the freedom of such adjustment has to be granted to owners under some given ranges.

Here's the first reason: optimized way for work strongly depends on conditions. Manufacture industries, which still carries over a half of total national GDP in South Korea, has the feature that more working time generally gurantees more benefits and utilities. 5-day work week would be best for most companies in these industries.

However, overworking would cause some physical & mental issues for service providers or office workers. Eventually, some of game developing teams have to "crunch" for weeks: working almost 24/6 before the release. [End of passage, due to timeout]

peerEssay:
In the past few years, there emerges a interesting debate about whether to eliminate paper books and go completely digital. With this change, students and readers would use e-readers or tablets instead of traditional books; or, they might could have the choice to select which material they prefer between digital and physical copies. This big trend has came from major publishers and educational institutes in different parts of Europe, aiming to reduce paper use and increase access to books and materials for each individuals. The main factor driving this interest in Japan is the statement by the current Education Minister, Yuki Nakamura, about initiating his plans for reorganizing educational resources this fiscal year.

He stated that during his term, he will implement a transition to digital books on a large scale and will introduced a mixed system — both digital and paper books will be available, but with a premium on paper copies. The core argument was maintaining the essence of reading, which has been questioned and challenged by several educators and scientists.

Yet nonetheless, I believe it is not only about choosing between paper and digital books. Personally, the focus should be on enhancing reading experiences, adjusted based on individual learner's needs, and this flexibility should be provided to stakeholders within defined limits.

Here's a primary reason: optimal reading methods largely depends on personal preferences. Student populations, that still comprise a large percentage of national demographic, benefit from accessing diverse formats for learning and comprehension. Both paper and digital options could serve well for different learners.

However, overdependence on digital devices might lead to some eye strain & attention issues for students or avid readers. Eventually, some of them may end up using both formats alternately actively.

The "Chusuck" holiday is just a month left. Like me, everyone will be starting to prepare for a long journey to their hometown: Searching for any rest train or bus seats, get enough oils for their cars, or maybe reserving an airplane ticket. Now let's think about how would we make the long marathon to our hometown if we didn't have all these automobiles. We might have to walk all the way down, which would take more than a week, for sure. As you can see, the automobile has improved our life a lot. I will show you some more examples throughout this passage. 

 Back in the days, when there was some important news in the country, it tooke a lot of times to get people know it since the country was too big to move around just with a horse or something. After the automobile came out, it became much easier to send recent news across the country. The best improvement that the automobile made is that we could save a lot of times.

 The automobile made our society way better, too. The shorter time taken to move means more chances to meet friends who lives in the opposite side of the country and more time for work or entertainment. This improved the social activity in human society and also the quality of human's life.

For conclusion, I can say that automobiles surely improved our modern life, and the human society. We should live with grateful minds toward the automobiles.

studentEssay:
Today, people have different needs, so there are many types of work. In Korea, most companies follow a 5-day work week, but many people want a 4-day work week. I think there are many benefits to a 4-day work week.

First, work-life balance has become much more important than in the past. Money is also important, but spending time with family, resting, and having time for personal development are even more valuable these days. Having only two days of personal time per week is not enough.

Second, efficiency is more important than spending long hours at work. I think concentrating for a short time and achieving the best results is the most effective way to work. In Europe, some companies have already adopted a 4-day work week because they believe efficiency is the most important factor.

Third, companies can hire more employees. With a 4-day work week, each person may earn slightly less, allowing companies to employ more people. More employees bring diverse ideas, which can help the company develop and innovate.

In conclusion, considering people’s needs and company development, a 4-day work week is a better choice.

Eating healthy is important for everyone, but it can be more vital for students. In college, many students eat fast food. I believe a healthy diet gives long-term benefits.

First, there [is] always many options to choose [healthier] food instead of junk food.. Eating right foods help students to concentrate better on their studies. But finding time to cook can be difficult, so quick healthy recipes can be good solution.

Second, maintaining a balanced diet can help prevent illnesses. Eating right can means students spend less time being sick and more time learning and having fun. Being sick can also lead to missing important classes, so meal planning is helpful.

Third, a healthy diet [encourages] better mood balance... In campus, students often feel stress and anxiety. Eating balanced diet have positive effects on mental health, reducing stress levels.

In conclusion, healthy eating is important for students’ life and studies.

studentEssay:
While science is growing, automobile has improved together. In modern life, almost people use automobile such as car, bus, taxi, and air plane. Although there has been some accident related with automobile, it doesn't mean that automobile must be prevented. Automobile significantly affect our society on positive side. There are three reasons why i argue like that.

First, Automobile can makes people be able to visit to places which are far from us. It helps people to meet a person who is important for them. And it even makes social link stronger through directly meeting other people. That is, Automobile can provide us positive effects by meeting some places which are far from us.

Second, Automobile is strongly related with transport. Transport is important industry for improving the nature. It makes country be able to sell or buy much stuff for other countries. And it helps people's life to be more fertile. Then, Automobile allows us to transport stuff to other natures

Lastly, Automobile occurs expansion of people sight to world. With automobiles, people can communicate with many experts in the world. In this progress, people share their opinion to many other people who are lived in places with other cultures compared with us. And it gives us world-wide sight.

Finally, there are many positive sides about automobile such as visiting other countries, transporting, and world-wide sight. Though there are some negative effect from automobile, but these positive effects can not be ignored. Conclusionly, automobile is important component for improving modern life.

peerEssay:
Pets have been always a part of human society. Almost people like to have pets, like dogs, cats, birds, and even exotic animals. These animals not only bring joy, but they also significantly affect our life on positive side. Here are three reasons why i argue like that.

Firstly, Pets can provide us with great feeling of comfort and companionship. It make us feel less lonely, and helps in reducing stress. Having a pet also encourages us to go outside and be active. That is, owning a pet can make our life more enjoyable by reducing loneliness and increasing happiness.

Secondly, Pets is strongly linked with routines. They require regular feeding, grooming, and exercise. This helps people to develop a sense of responsibility and time management. Then, pets teach us the importance of caring for other beings.

Lastly, Children can benefits from having pets in the home. They learn empathy and how to take care of their furry friends. Sometimes, it even help improve their social skills as they communicate with their pet. Thus, pets contribute to personal development in children.

In the end, owning pets have many advantages such as comfort, routine, and learning. Though having pets come with some responsibility, but these positive effects can not be ignored. Conclusionly, pets are important component for enhancing our daily life.

studentEssay:
Good roommates are very important in the KAIST life. Because we spend a lot of time with them, we make and occur several problems and situations. There are various conditions to be a good roommate. 
First, we have to be quiet. Making big sounds give stress to other people, so it have to make less noise and talk smally after midnight. For example, I can't sleep when other sounds hear to me. Therefore to maintain a quiet place is nice to our mates. 
Second, we have to be kind. We and our roommates are different person, so we think and live different. Every human has own life or sleep cycle and we must not break them. Respect other's life pattern and don't bother when they are sleeping or studying.
Third, we have to be clear. The rooms are not my own places. It's our places, so we should clean beds, desk, chair etc. Also we take a shower everyday for them. If we don't wash, they may watch our dirty faces. To be clean man or woman is one of the great reasons about being a wonderful roommates.
Lastly, we have to be careful. Rooms are our living spaces, so it is very personal and individual. You must be careful when you do something like visit other rooms.
In my opinion, those are important for live together. With four qualities, you can be a perfect roommates!

In my opinion, students have better to study abroad. First, students can encounter new cultures and understand the value of other cultures. When students go abroad, they eat strange traditional food and live in the building built by their traditional method. While experiencing other culture, students can comprehend that not only own country, but also other countries have various cultures and those cultures are valuable to respect. Second, students also can experience new learning methods. There are many countries in the world, some countries mainly debate, others take quiz or test, and the other give questions during lecture. Although all these learning methods have own advantages and side effects, experiencing lots of learning ways make students have rich mindset. While studying, students consider the situation or events broadly and deeply. Third, students can meet a lot of people. Students encounter people who use different language and have different mindset. While students take dialogue with them, students can learn their culture, language and mindset indirectly, and these are hard to learn in student's own country. 
In conclusion, students can encounter new cultures, studying a variety of learning method and meet new friends. All these are helpful for students

studentEssay:
In recent days, there rises an hot issue about whether to reduce working days, from five to four days a week. Under this new system, employees would work from Monday to Thursday or from Tuesday to Friday; otherwise, you may be able to choose which day to take a rest between weekdays. It has been a big trend spread from big tech and venture corporations in some regions of United States, in the direction of cutting working hours and helping utilization of each workers. The main reason for the uprising attention in Korea is the announcement of current(21st) Korean president, Lee Jae-Myeong, for introducing his promises for the president election held in this year.

He said that during his period, he would give a renewal of work time into 4-day work week ultimately, and would get started the shift into 4.5-day work week — Mon. to Thurs. are just the same, and finish a work week at noon, on Friday — until the next year. His keypoint was that there would be no deduction of salary, so he has been offended and criticized from many business runners and experts in economics.

But though, I think it is not the most important thing about these arguments to simply choose between 4-day and 5-day. In my opinion, work week needs to be adjusted with considering each company's condition, and the freedom of such adjustment has to be granted to owners under some given ranges.

Here's the first reason; optimized way for work strongly depends on conditions. Manufacture industries, which still carries over a half of total national GDP in South Korea, has the feature that more working time generally gurantees more benefits and utilities. 5-day work week would be best for most companies in these industries.

However, overworking would cause some physical & mental issues for service providers or office workers. Eventually, some of game developing teams have to "crunch" for weeks, which means to work almost 24/7 before the release. [End of passage, due to timeout]

peerEssay:
Recently, there emerges an new challenge on if to reduce school days, from five to four days a week. Through this new approach, students might study from Monday to Thursday or from Tuesday to Friday, otherwise, you could choose which day to have off during the weekdays. It is a major trend from well-known educational institutions in some areas of United States, in the direction of lowering school hours and enhancing performance of each student. The main factor for the growing curiosity in Japan is the announcement of present (21st) Japanese prime minister, Suzuki Kaito, for incorporating his plans for the prime minister election happening this year.

He declared that during his tenure, he will provide a revision of school time into 4-day school week ultimately, and would be started the shift into 4.5-day school week — Mon. to Thurs. are unchanged, and end a school week at midday, on Friday — until the next year. His keypoint was that there will be no reduction of education quality, so he was opposed and criticized from many educators and authorities in education.

But however, I believe it is not the most critical aspect of these discussions to simply select between 4-day and 5-day. In my view, school week needs to be aligned with considering each school's condition, and the flexibility of such alignment has to be allowed to educators within some given limits.

Here's one reason; the ideal way for teaching strongly relies on circumstances. Academic institutions, which still provides over a half of total educational value in Japan, has the feature that more studying generally ensures more success and achievements. 5-day school week would be ideal for most schools in these systems.

Still, extra study would cause some mental & physical problems for high schoolers or elementary students. Finally, some of teachers teams need to "cram" for weeks, which means to work almost every day before exams.

studentEssay:
While science is growing, automobile has improved together. In modern life, almost people use automobile such as car, bus, taxi, and air plane. Although there has been some accident related with automobile, it doesn't mean that automobile must be prevented. Automobile significantly affect our society on positive side. There are three reasons why i argue like that.

First, Automobile can makes people be able to visit to places which are far from us. It helps people to meet a person who is important for them. And it even makes social link stronger through directly meeting other people. That is, Automobile can provide us positive effects by meeting some places which are far from us.

Second, Automobile is strongly related with transport. Transport is important industry for improving the nature. It makes country be able to sell or buy much stuff for other countries. And it helps people's life to be more fertile. Then, Automobile allows us to transport stuff to other natures

Lastly, Automobile occurs expansion of people sight to world. With automobiles, people can communicate with many experts in the world. In this progress, people share their opinion to many other people who are lived in places with other cultures compared with us. And it gives us world-wide sight.

Finally, there are many positive sides about automobile such as visiting other countries, transporting, and world-wide sight. Though there are some negative effect from automobile, but these positive effects can not be ignored. Conclusionly, automobile is important component for improving modern life.

peerEssay:
Technology is advancing rapidly, and robotics has changed along with it. In today's world, almost machines are used by people such as robots, computers, phones, and televisions. Although robotics has caused some issues like job loss, it does not mean their development should stop. Robotics greatly affect our world on positive side. There are three reasons why I believe so.

First, robotics can increase efficiency in production processes. It allows factories to produce more products in a shorter time. And it even makes production more precise by reducing error rates. That is, robotics can bring us benefits by increasing productivity in various industries.

Second, robotics is closely linked with innovation. Innovation improves quality of life by providing new solutions. It helps countries develop technologies that improve people's daily life. Then, robotics provide us with new tools that make life easier.

Lastly, robotics offers a broader perspective on the future. With robotics, people can explore new possibilities. In this journey, people learn and share new technologies with other people from different backgrounds than us. And it opens up our world to new ideas.

Finally, robotics have many positive contributions such as increasing efficiency, driving innovation, and expanding future visions. Although there are some challenges from robotics, but its benefits are undeniable. Conclusionly, robotics plays important role in shaping modern society.

studentEssay:
Good roommates are very important in the KAIST life. Because we spend a lot of time with them, we make and occur several problems and situations. There are various conditions to be a good roommate. 
First, we have to be quiet. Making big sounds give stress to other people, so it have to make less noise and talk smally after midnight. For example, I can't sleep when other sounds hear to me. Therefore to maintain a quiet place is nice to our mates. 
Second, we have to be kind. We and our roommates are different person, so we think and live different. Every human has own life or sleep cycle and we must not break them. Respect other's life pattern and don't bother when they are sleeping or studying.
Third, we have to be clear. The rooms are not my own places. It's our places, so we should clean beds, desk, chair etc. Also we take a shower everyday for them. If we don't wash, they may watch our dirty faces. To be clean man or woman is one of the great reasons about being a wonderful roommates.
Lastly, we have to be careful. Rooms are our living spaces, so it is very personal and individual. You must be careful when you do something like visit other rooms.
In my opinion, those are important for live together. With four qualities, you can be a perfect roommates!

Reading books is a good hobby for many people. Because books come in many genres, we get learn a lot of subjects and adventures. There are different reasons to read books.
To start, it give knowledge. Books is full of information, and it open up new worlds to understand. For instance, learning history teach us about past events.

The reading passage presents three potential solutions to prevent the extinction of the Torreya tree. However, the professor in the lecture disagrees with all of them and provides reasons why they are unlikely to be effective.
First, the reading suggests replanting the Torreya tree in its original habitat in Florida, where a unique microclimate once supported its growth. However, the professor points out that making the reintroduction of the tree to this area would be ineffective because this microclimate no longer exists due to climate change.
Second, the reading proposes relocating the Torreya tree to a colder region in the north, assuming that it may thrive in such a climate. The professor counters this by citing the example of the black locust tree, which grew excessively and caused damage to the local ecosystem after being moved to a new area.
Finally, the reading recommends cultivating the Torreya tree in research centers, enabling scientists to protect and study it. Nevertheless, the professor argues that trees grown in controlled environments tend to lose their natural resistance to diseases. Furthermore, replicating the extensive and diverse conditions required for the tree’s survival in the wild is highly challenging.
In conclusion, current team should work harder to find the solution to preventing the extinction of Torreya tree!

studentEssay:
In recent days, there rises an hot issue about whether to reduce working days, from five to four days a week. Under this new system, employees would work from Monday to Thursday or from Tuesday to Friday; otherwise, you may be able to choose which day to take a rest between weekdays. It has been a big trend spread from big tech and venture corporations in some regions of United States, in the direction of cutting working hours and helping utilization of each workers. The main reason for the uprising attention in Korea is the announcement of current(21st) Korean president, Lee Jae-Myeong, for introducing his promises for the president election held in this year.

He said that during his period, he would give a renewal of work time into 4-day work week ultimately, and would get started the shift into 4.5-day work week — Mon. to Thurs. are just the same, and finish a work week at noon, on Friday — until the next year. His keypoint was that there would be no deduction of salary, so he has been offended and criticized from many business runners and experts in economics.

But though, I think it is not the most important thing about these arguments to simply choose between 4-day and 5-day. In my opinion, work week needs to be adjusted with considering each company's condition, and the freedom of such adjustment has to be granted to owners under some given ranges.

Here's the first reason; optimized way for work strongly depends on conditions. Manufacture industries, which still carries over a half of total national GDP in South Korea, has the feature that more working time generally gurantees more benefits and utilities. 5-day work week would be best for most companies in these industries.

However, overworking would cause some physical & mental issues for service providers or office workers. Eventually, some of game developing teams have to "crunch" for weeks, which means to work almost 24/7 before the release. [End of passage, due to timeout]

peerEssay:
The discussion of climate change has become important last years. Many governments and organizations discuss how to reduce the carbon footprints, but it still being debated topic with unclear consensus. People suggest planting trees as a solution for balance the increasing carbon dioxide, but lack clear action plans exist. The governments need to draw policies that focus on green energies and sustainability, which support can be insightful for every individual. The priority of using renewable source energies like solar and wind must be increased.

However, the action plans has sometimes lacked enough detail to execute effectively. More clear, precise strategies are needed, and these strategies must involve multiple sectors and collaboration internationally. The carbon neutral projects must partner with industries for tangible impact development. Despite this, stakeholders often express concern about the economic impacts of going green.

Many believe it's a costly change norms in energy sector will face challenges. Though, better cooperation with international bodies can allocate resources efficiently and create more effective results rather than isolated attempts.

To conclude, combatting climate change requires comprehensive approach. One can't just rely on isolated efforts, like tree planting alone. Strong government policies interconnected with global efforts is necessary to achieve broader, lasting results.

studentEssay:
TITLE: There should be a 4-day work week.

Many foreign workers in Korea have a difficulty in something. Can you guess what it is? It’s working hour (time). They usually have had hard time to adopt Korea working system. Korea works too much. Even though it decreased than before, the A of Korean work up to 55 hours per week. So, today, I’ll discuss why There should be a 4-day work week. Now, I’ll give you more details.

To begin with, we can do more in work if we get relax more. Think about When you take over the night studying. Was the efficiency good? Maybe not. It’s same as workers. They should get relax more, take a sleep and then come to work place with high quality of energy and condition.

Secondly, if there is a 4-day work week, the increasing of spending would be expected. Spending could be a good for economics. Many can cycle and small marketers can sell more things. For example, Past in Korea, when it changed to 5-day work week from 6-day work week, Many people worried that workers efficiency will get down. However, people spend a lot of time and Money so the economics could be circulated.

Lastly, it can be welfare to workers time take off one day. They do not need to use their personal holiday to their work place. Everybody get a break. So, people can live more happily.

Then, how to make it for real? I’ll suggest some ways to bring it.
First way: work free on wednesday. If we take a break on wednesday, we only work two days directly. Wednesday is profit for holiday because it located middle of weeks days.
Second way: replace work free days zig-zag. For example, people whose birth-year ends with 0,5 → Mon, 1,6 → Tue, 2,7 → Wednesday, 3,8 → Thur, 4,9 → Fri work free.
